IL CONTE
Contessa, perdono!
LA CONTESSA
Più docile io sono,
e dico di sì.
TUTTI
Ah, tutti contenti
saremo così.
Questo giorno di tormenti,
di capricci, e di follia,
in contenti e in allegria
solo amor può terminar.
Sposi, amici, al ballo, al gioco,
alle mine date foco!
Ed al suon di lieta marcia
corriam tutti a festeggiar! 
COUNT
My Countess, forgive me.
COUNTESS
I am kinder:
I will say "Yes." ALL
Then let us all
Be happy.
This day of torment,
Of caprices and folly,
Love can end
Only in contentment and joy.
Lovers and friends, let's round things off
In dancing and pleasure,
And to the sound of a gay march
Let's hasten to the revelry.

Karl Gottfried Hagen (1749-1829) war ein deutscher Apotheker, der mit seinem Lehrbuch der Apothekerkunst einen Hit landete. Das Werk erschien in 8 Auflagen und  gilt als erstes Lehrbuch der Pharmazie. Es half mit, den Übergang vom handwerklichen zum akademischen Apotheker zu festigten.
Darin beschreibt er unter anderem die Verarbeitung von Myrrhe, die am besten in Bier gelöst werden könne.

On New Year’s Day, 1802, Thomas Jefferson stood in the doorway of the President’s House to receive a most unusual gift from the citizens of Cheshire, Massachusetts:
an enormous wheel of cheese, measuring more than 4 feet (1.2 m)  in diameter and weighing an estimated 1,235 pounds (560 kg).
Cheese production began in the summer of 1801 and milk from every cow in Cheshire - approximately 900 cows - was used to create this colossal cheese.
It was presented to Jefferson at the President’s House after a 500 miles trip in horse-drawn sleigh, and remained there for over two years, eventually being replaced by the "Mammoth Loaf," a large loaf of bread made by the United States Navy 🧀

The first American to be buried at Arlington National Cemetery⁣
⁣
Private William Christman was a Civil War Union Army Soldier. He was living as a young farm boy from Monroe County, Pennsylvania, when the Civil War began in April 1861. After two years of following the fortunes of the war, he eventually was compelled to enlist by the large bonuses offered by officials, which would help his family greatly. On March 24, 1864 he was officially mustered in as a recruit Private in Company G, 67th Pennsylvania Volunteer Infantry. Unfortunately, his service would prove to be brief, for at the end of April 1864 he was stricken by a case of rubella. His conditioned worsened, and he was transported from the regimental hospital to the Lincoln United States Army General Hospital in Washington, DC. There on May 11, 1864 he succumbed to his ailments, one of 153 men from his regiment to die from disease during the war. On May 13, 1864 he was buried in the grounds of Arlington House, the home of Confederate General Robert E. Lee, whose residence was taken over by Union forces early in the war, and in whose land Union Army Quartermaster General Montgomery C. Meigs had designated as a military cemetery, becoming the first soldier to be buried in what officially became Arlington National Cemetery.⁣

Brigham Young - June 1, 1801 – August 29, 1877, was an American religious leader, politician, and settler. He was the second president of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints (LDS Church) from 1847 until his death in 1877. He founded Salt Lake City and he served as the first governor of the Utah Territory. Young was a polygamist, marrying a total of 55 wives, 54 of them after he converted to Mormonism.

И сомневаюсь, что при устройстве на обычную работу, тебя спросят: "А какие у тебя мечты?", признают твои заслуги, будут дарить подарки, научат верить в себя и раскрывать твои таланты. Много желаний сбылось, много трудностей пришлось преодолеть! Я рада, что могу совмещать несколько видов деятельности ( и тоже исполнилось желание, везде хорошие коллективы) постоянно обучаться в разных направлениях. И самое ГЛАВНОЕ, первую очередь растить дочку🤱, ведь это невероятное счастье. Обращайтесь! научу  как ☝️ Ведь дорогу осилит идущий #marykayдмитров

#today #19 #Maggio #1802 L'Ordine #nazionale della Legion d'onore (#Ordre #national de la #Légion d'#honneur, denominazione originale in lingua francese) è un ordine cavalleresco istituito il 19 maggio 1802 da #NapoleoneBonaparte, primo console della Prima repubblica francese.
È l'onorificenza più alta attribuita dalla #Repubblica #francese #🇫🇷 #Napoleone, da #imperatore, utilizzò spesso sulla propria #divisa la #gran #Croce #🖤 dell'Ordine della Legion d'onore.Secondo alcune fonti, Napoleone dichiarò: On appelle ça des hochets, je sais, on l'a dit déjà. Et bien, j'ai répondu que c'est avec des hochets que l'on mène les #hommes. ("Li chiamano ciucciotti, lo so e me lo hanno già detto. Ebbene, ho risposto che è con dei ciucciotti che si comandano gli #uomini")
L'ordine fu di fatto la prima onorificenza al merito, dal momento , la Legion d'onore era conferita senza alcuna distinzione sociale, contando esclusivamente il valore e i meriti personali. Le insegne dei precedenti ordini. #wikipedia

Nupcias del Libertador

En la villa de Madrid a veinte y seis días del mes de mayo de mil ochocientos dos, en la Iglesia Parroquial de Sn. Josef, yo, Don Isidro Bonifacio Romano, Teniente mayor de Cura de la misma habiendo procedido despacho del señor Dr. Juan Bautista de Expeleta, Pro. Vicario Ecco. De esta referida villa y su partido. Dado en veinte del propio mes y año, refrendado de Diego Alonso Martín, su notario, por el que consta haberse dispensado las tres amonestaciones que proviene el Sto. Concilio de Trento, por la justa causas que concurrieron para ello; recibidos los justos consentimientos; hechas las demás preguntas y requisitos necesarios y no habiendo resultado impedimento alguno desposé in Facie Eclesial, por palabras del presente que hacen verdadero y lexmo matrimonio a Don Simón Bolívar, natural de la ciudad y Obispado de Caracas en América, hijo de Don Juan Vicente Bolívar y de Doña María de la Concepción Palacios (ya difuntos) con Doña María Teresa Rodríguez del Toro, natural de esta referida villa, hija de Don Bernardo Rodríguez del Toro y Ascanio y de Doña Benita Alaiza Medrano (ya difunta) precedido los requisitos necesarios, se hallaron presente por testigos Don Pedro Rodríguez del Toro, el señor Marqués de Inicio y otros, juntamente los velé y di las bendiciones nupciales según el ritual y lo firmé.

On May 18th, 1802, Napoleon Bonaparte formed the Legion d’honneur. During the French Revolution, all the French orders of chivalry were abolished and replaced with Weapons of Honour instead, ceremonial weapons awarded for service or assistance to the country. However, Napoleon wanted to create some sort of reward to commend civilians and soldiers. He therefore established the Legion of Honour. This body was not an order of chivalry, however it did use the organisation of the old French orders of chivalry. Today the Legion of Honour is France’s highest order of merit.

Un día como hoy pero de 1825 muere en Buenos Aires Domingo French. En 1802, French se transformó en el primer cartero de Buenos Aires. Durante la primera invasión inglesa organizó, junto a Juan Martín de Pueyrredón, el cuerpo de Húsares. Fue uno de los más entusiastas patriotas durante los sucesos de Mayo de 1810 y repartió las famosas cintitas para distinguir a los patriotas. Producida la revolución, la Junta le encomendó la creación de un cuerpo de infantería. French acompañó a Castelli a Córdoba e hizo ejecutar la sentencia contra Liniers y sus cómplices. Como miembro de la tendencia morenista, fue separado de la Junta de Gobierno por los saavedristas en abril de 1811 y enviado al destierro en la Patagonia. Regresó en 1812 y se reintegró al ejército. Participó en el sitio de Montevideo en 1814. En 1817 tuvo que marchar al exilio en los Estados Unidos junto a Manuel Dorrego por oponerse a la política del Directorio, pero logró regresar en 1819. Había nacido en Buenos Aires el 21 de noviembre de 1774.

Nupcias del Libertador

En la villa de Madrid a veinte y seis días del mes de mayo de mil ochocientos dos, en la Iglesia Parroquial de Sn. Josef, yo, Don Isidro Bonifacio Romano, Teniente mayor de Cura de la misma habiendo procedido despacho del señor Dr. Juan Bautista de Expeleta, Pro. Vicario Ecco. De esta referida villa y su partido. Dado en veinte del propio mes y año, refrendado de Diego Alonso Martín, su notario, por el que consta haberse dispensado las tres amonestaciones que proviene el Sto. Concilio de Trento, por la justa causas que concurrieron para ello; recibidos los justos consentimientos; hechas las demás preguntas y requisitos necesarios y no habiendo resultado impedimento alguno desposé in Facie Eclesial, por palabras del presente que hacen verdadero y lexmo matrimonio a Don Simón Bolívar, natural de la ciudad y Obispado de Caracas en América, hijo de Don Juan Vicente Bolívar y de Doña María de la Concepción Palacios (ya difuntos) con Doña María Teresa Rodríguez del Toro, natural de esta referida villa, hija de Don Bernardo Rodríguez del Toro y Ascanio y de Doña Benita Alaiza Medrano (ya difunta) precedido los requisitos necesarios, se hallaron presente por testigos Don Pedro Rodríguez del Toro, el señor Marqués de Inicio y otros, juntamente los velé y di las bendiciones nupciales según el ritual y lo firmé.

Don Isidro Bonifacio Romano

.

.
“…el contrayente Manuel Angulo, dando por causa para casarse -con la ya mencionada Nicolasa Vargas- el haberla desflorado y dejándole prole (aunque todavía en el vientre) y quiere remediarlo…”.
.
1802 Marriage record in San Juan (Mérida, Venezuela):
.
“…first banns of marriage for Manuel Angulo’s marriage with Nicolasa Vargas…”.
.
“…for the boyfriend had intercourse with a sister-in-law, and the girlfriend with a brother-in-law…”.
.
“…the fiancé Manuel Angulo, giving reasons for getting married -with the aforementioned Nicolasa Vargas- for having deflowered her and leaving her offspring (though still in her belly) and wants to remedy it…”.
.

항상 은 제품 주문하는 열매맘님께 주문 했는데 이번에도 역시 세밀하게 정성스럽게 만들어서 보내주셨어요. 은이라서 무게가 많이 나갈까 걱정했는데 이전에 했던 목걸이보다 4-5그람 차이 밖에 안나서 하나도 안 무거워요. 이전에 했던 건 6.1그람이였는데 지금 은목걸이는 9그람? 10그람 정도 밖에 안되서 부담안되고 너무 좋아요. 팬던트는 백원짜리 동전 크기예요. 은이라서 어느 옷을 입던지 다 잘 어울리고, 예쁘고 아주 대만족 완전 만족입니다.🙂

Día Mundial del Cóctel 
Un 13 de mayo de 1806, el periódico neoyorquino "The Balance and Columbian Repository" público por primera vez la definición de la palabra Cocktail. Siete días antes, la palabra aparecía en un artículo relacionado a un candidato político. Un lector del periódico le pide al editor la definición de esta palabra. "Cocktail es una bebida estimulante a base de espitituosos de todo tipo, azúcar, agua y bitters; bittered y sling, y se supone que es una excelente poción para la campaña electoral, porque da brío al corazón a la vez que enturbia la cabeza"

La alimentacion complementaria AC 🧀🌭🌮🌯🍮🍰🍔🍤🍗🍖 Es muy importante porque de esto depende de que el bebe coma bien o mal 😊. La AC es toda una experiencia para tanto para el pequeño como para la mamá 👶😉, porque es ahí donde comenzara a reconocer aromas, texturas, formas, etc. Por ende, es necesario dejarlo que experimente, dejarlo que juegue con la comida 💛. Porque de este modo le encantará la hora de comer y cuando crezca comera de lo mejor💖. Es importante darles los alimentos ricos en hierro ya que esto les evitara que en un futuro tenga anemia.💪 NOTA 👀: Es importante utilizar la regla de tres, iniciar con un alimento durante tres dias 🚼 y despues cambiarle por otro.

TENER EN CUENTA 💫: que la AC es decisión de la mama y tu bebe y de nadie mas, tu tienes todo el derecho en mandar en su alimentacion de tu hijo, disfruta mucho de esta etapa y hazla la mas divertida para los dos 👪.

Wie in alten Zeiten: Heute haben unsere Vereinsmitglieder Robert und Alexander Heyne zusammen mit Rolf-Peter Graf in #Kapellendorf am Denkmal auf dem Sperlingsberg in einem Arbeitseinsatz Beschilderungen angebracht. Angegeben sind darauf die Richtung sowie die Entfernung zu den einzelnen Ortschaften vom aktuellen Standpunkt, so dass interessierte Besucher sich einen guten Überblick über die Orte des Geschehens von #1806 verschaffen können. Just like old times:  Today, our members Robert and Alexander Heyne, together with Rolf-Peter Graf in Kapellendorf, have put up signs at the monument on the Sperlingsberg in a work assignment.  They show the direction and the distance to the individual villages from the current point of view, so that interested visitors can get a good overview of the places of the events of #1806. #lebendigegeschichte #geschichteerleben #denkmalpflege #gelebtegeschichte #thüringenerleben #thuringia #jena #jenaauerstedt #battleofjena #jena1806 #thüringen #arbeitsgemeinschaft

5.13.1806 - the date the word “cocktail” was first found in print.

Cocktails completely changed the course of my life when I was 21 years old. They took a college student with no direction and transformed me into someone dedicated to trying new spirits, intrigued with balancing the sweet, sour and bitter, and compelled with bringing culinary flavors to liquid form. The cocktail changed history and most certainly changed me. It seems only kismet now that I work with a collective of likeminded people honoring that day in 1806.

#1806 ਤੋਂ ਲੈ ਕੇ #1841 ਤੱਕ 4 ਵਾਰੀ ਤਿੱਬਤ ਨੂੰ ਫਤਹਿ ਕਰਨ ਵਾਲਾ ਮਹਾਰਾਜਾ ਰਣਜੀਤ ਸਿੰਘ ਦੀ ਫੌਜ ਵਿੱਚ ਦੁਨੀਆਂ ਦਾ ਪਹਿਲਾ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਹੈ: * ਜਰਨਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਸਿੰਘ * (ਜਿਸਦੇ ਮਾਸ ਦੀ ਬੋਟੀ-ਬੋਟੀ ਤੱਕ ਵਿਕੀ) ਤਿੱਬਤ ਦੇ ਵਿੱਚ ਇੱਕ ਟੋਏਓ ਨਾਮ ਦਾ ਕਬੀਲਾ ਹੈ,ਉੱਥੇ ਬੇਸ਼ੱਕ ਅੱਜ ਬੋਧੀ ਲੋਕ ਰਹਿੰਦੇ ਹਨ, ਪਰ ਉੱਥੇ ਇੱਕ ਪਿੰਡ ਹੈ ਜਿਸਦਾ ਨਾਂ ਹੈ: ਟਕਲਾਕੋਟ...ਉੱਥੇ ਜੇਕਰ ਜਾ ਕੇ ਪੁੱਛੀਏ ਕਿ ਅਸੀਂ ਜਰਨਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਸਿੰਘ ਦੀ ਸਮਾਧ ਦੇਖਣੀ ਹੈ ਤਾਂ.... ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਸਮਝ ਨਹੀਂ ਆਉਂਦੀ ਕਿਉਂਕਿ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਲੋਕਾਂ ਦੀ ਭਾਸ਼ਾ ਹੋਰ ਹੈ

ਪਰ ਜਦੋਂ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਦਾ ਨਾਂ ਸੁਣਨਗੇ!... ਤਾਂ ਉਹ ਤੁਹਾਡੀ ਪੱਗ ਵੱਲ ਦੇਖ ਕੇ ਇਸ਼ਾਰਾ ਕਰਦੇ ਹੋਏ ਕਹਿਣਗੇ ਕਿ : ਇਵੇਂ ਦਾ ਜਦੋਂ ਤੁਸੀਂ ਯੈੱਸ ਕਹੋਂਗੇ!.. ਤਾਂ ਉਹ ਬਹੁਤ ਖੁਸ਼ ਹੋ ਕੇ ਕਹਿੰਦੇ ਨੇ ਕਿ: ਸਿੰਘਲਾਬਾਚੋਰਟਨ!.... ਸਿੰਘਲਾਬਾਚੋਰਟਨ!..... ਭਾਵ : ਜਿੱਥੇ ਸ਼ੇਰ ਸੁੱਤਾ ਪਿਆ ਹੈ! ਤੁਸੀਂ ਉੱਥੇ ਜਾਣਾ ਹੈ!
ਫਿਰ ਤੁਹਾਡਾ ਹੱਥ ਪਕੜ ਕੇ ਲੈ ਜਾਣਗੇ ਜਿੱਥੇ ਸਾਡੀ ਕੌਮ ਦਾ ਸ਼ੇਰ ਸੁੱਤਾ ਪਿਆ ਹੈ। ਉਹ ਸ਼ੇਰ ਜਿਸਨੇ ਤਿੱਬਤ, ਖਦੂੰਗਲਾ, ਜੁਜੀਲਾ,ਕਾਰਗਲ, ਲੇਹ, ਨਿੰਮੁ, ਲਦਾਖ, ਟੋਏਉ, ਮਾਨ ਸਰੋਵਰ ਤੱਕ ਸਿੱਖ ਰਾਜ ਕਾਇਮ ਕੀਤਾ। 12/ਦਸੰਬਰ/1841 ਨੂੰ ਟਕਲਾਕੋਟ ਦੇ ਮੈਦਾਨੇ-ਜੰਗ ਵਿੱਚ ਉਸ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਨੂੰ ਗੋਲੀ ਵੱਜੀ ਸੀ। 12/ਦਸੰਬਰ ਨੂੰ ਉਸ ਦਿਨ ਦਾ ਤਾਪਮਾਨ -34°ਸੀ ਜਿੱਥੇ ਉਹ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਲੜ ਰਿਹਾ ਸੀ। ਗੋਲੀ ਲੱਗਣ ਕਾਰਨ ਘੋੜੇ ਤੋਂ ਜ਼ਮੀਨ ਤੇ ਡਿੱਗਦਾ ਹੈ ਤੇ ਤਿੱਬਤੀ ਭਾਸ਼ਾ ਵਿੱਚ ਵੁੰਗ ਭਾਵ (ਉਹ ਛੋਟਾ ਬਰਛਾ ਜਿਹੜਾ ਦੂਰ ਤੋ ਚਲਾਇਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ) ਜਨਰਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਦੀ ਸ਼ਾਤੀ ਵਿਚੋਂ ਆਰ-ਪਾਰ ਕਰ ਦਿੱਤਾ ਗਿਆ ਤੇ ਜ਼ਮੀਨ ਤੇ ਉਸਦੀ ਤਕਰੀਬਨ ਸਵੇਰੇ 9/10 ਵਜੇ ਸ਼ਹੀਦੀ ਹੋ ਗਈ...
ਇਸ ਲੜਾਈ ਵਿੱਚ 12,000 ਸਿੱਖ ਸ਼ਹੀਦ ਹੋਇਆ ਸੀ। ਜਰਨਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਦੀ ਸ਼ਹੀਦੀ ਤੋਂ ਬਾਅਦ 12:00 ਵਜੇ ਫਿਰ 2 ਤਿੱਬਤੀ ਕਬੀਲਿਆਂ (ਟਕਲਾਕੋਟ ਤੇ ਟੋਏਉ ਟਰੇਪ) ਦੀ ਆਪਸ ਵਿੱਚ ਲੜਾਈ ਸ਼ੁਰੂ ਹੋ ਜਾਂਦੀ ਹੈ। ਪਰ ਲੜਾਈ ਕਿਉਂ ਹੋ ਰਹੀ ਹੈ! ਕਿਉਂਕਿ!.. ਇੱਕ ਕਬੀਲਾ ਕਹਿ ਰਿਹਾ ਹੈ ਕਿ ਜਨਰਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਦੀ ਲਾਸ਼ ਅਸੀਂ ਲੈਣੀ ਹੈ..... ਤੇ ਦੂਜਾ ਕਹਿ ਰਿਹਾ ਹੈ ਕਿ ਲਾਸ਼ ਅਸੀਂ ਲੈਣੀ ਹੈ..... ਹੁਣ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਦੀ ਲਾਸ਼ ਨੂੰ ਵੰਡਣ ਤੇ ਲੜਾਈ ਹੋ ਗਈ। 
ਸੋਚਣ ਵਾਲੀ ਗੱਲ ਹੈ ਕਿ ਹੁਣ ਦੁਸ਼ਮਣ ਮਰਿਆ ਪਿਆ ਹੈ...ਜਿਥੇ ਮਰਜੀ ਸੁੱਟ ਦਿਓ, ਲਾਸ਼ ਬਰਫ਼ ਵਿਚ ਪਈ ਹੈ, ਫਿਰ ਲੜਾਈ ਕਿਉਂ ਹੋ ਰਹੀ ਹੈ! .... ਕਿਉਂਕਿ ਉਹ ਕਬੀਲੇ ਦੇ ਲੋਕ ਯਕੀਨ ਕਰਦੇ ਨੇ ਕਿ ਜੇਕਰ ਸ਼ੇਰ ਦਾ ਮਾਸ ਘਰ ਵਿੱਚ ਰੱਖਿਆ ਜਾਵੇ ਤਾਂ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦੇ ਬੱਚੇ ਬਹਾਦਰ ਜਨਮ ਲੈਂਦੇ ਨੇਂ.... ਤੇ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਨੇ ਦੇਖਿਆ ਕਿ ਇਹ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਇੰਨੀ ਜਿਆਦਾ ਬਹਾਦਰੀ ਦੇ ਨਾਲ ਲੜਿਆ ਕਿ ਇਸਦੇ ਸਾਹਮਣੇ ਤਾਂ ਸ਼ੇਰ ਕੁੱਝ ਵੀ ਨਹੀਂ ਹੈ!... ਅਸੀਂ ਤਾਂ ਇਸਦਾ ਮਾਸ ਹੀ ਘਰ ਵਿੱਚ ਰੱਖਣਾ ਹੈ। ਇਹ ਲੜਾਈ ਉਸਦੇ ਮਾਸ ਵੰਡਣ ਤੋਂ ਹੋ ਰਹੀ ਹੈ.... ਅਖ਼ੀਰ!.. ਇੱਕ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦੇ ਇੱਕ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਨੇ ਫੈਸਲਾ ਲਿਆ ਕਿ: “ਲੜੋ ਨਾ, ਆਪਾਂ ਇਸ ਦੀ ਲਾਸ਼ ਦਾ ਮੁੱਲ ਪਾ ਕੇ ਵੰਡ ਲੈਂਦੇ ਹਾਂ।”

ਸੋਚਣ ਵਾਲੀ ਗੱਲ ਹੈ ਕਿ ਹੁਣ ਦੁਸ਼ਮਣ ਮਰਿਆ ਪਿਆ ਹੈ...ਜਿਥੇ ਮਰਜੀ ਸੁੱਟ ਦਿਓ, ਲਾਸ਼ ਬਰਫ਼ ਵਿਚ ਪਈ ਹੈ, ਫਿਰ ਲੜਾਈ ਕਿਉਂ ਹੋ ਰਹੀ ਹੈ! .... ਕਿਉਂਕਿ ਉਹ ਕਬੀਲੇ ਦੇ ਲੋਕ ਯਕੀਨ ਕਰਦੇ ਨੇ ਕਿ ਜੇਕਰ ਸ਼ੇਰ ਦਾ ਮਾਸ ਘਰ ਵਿੱਚ ਰੱਖਿਆ ਜਾਵੇ ਤਾਂ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦੇ ਬੱਚੇ ਬਹਾਦਰ ਜਨਮ ਲੈਂਦੇ ਨੇਂ.... ਤੇ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਨੇ ਦੇਖਿਆ ਕਿ ਇਹ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਜੋਰਾਵਰ ਇੰਨੀ ਜਿਆਦਾ ਬਹਾਦਰੀ ਦੇ ਨਾਲ ਲੜਿਆ ਕਿ ਇਸਦੇ ਸਾਹਮਣੇ ਤਾਂ ਸ਼ੇਰ ਕੁੱਝ ਵੀ ਨਹੀਂ ਹੈ!... ਅਸੀਂ ਤਾਂ ਇਸਦਾ ਮਾਸ ਹੀ ਘਰ ਵਿੱਚ ਰੱਖਣਾ ਹੈ। ਇਹ ਲੜਾਈ ਉਸਦੇ ਮਾਸ ਵੰਡਣ ਤੋਂ ਹੋ ਰਹੀ ਹੈ.... ਅਖ਼ੀਰ!.. ਇੱਕ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦੇ ਇੱਕ ਜਰਨੈਲ ਨੇ ਫੈਸਲਾ ਲਿਆ ਕਿ: “ਲੜੋ ਨਾ, ਆਪਾਂ ਇਸ ਦੀ ਲਾਸ਼ ਦਾ ਮੁੱਲ ਪਾ ਕੇ ਵੰਡ ਲੈਂਦੇ ਹਾਂ।”

Paciente submetido a tratamento com eletrochoques no século XIX.

A imagem em questão mostra o famoso neurologista Guillaume-Benjamin-Amand Duchenne (1806-1875), juntamente com seu assistente, aplicando eletrochoque em um de seus pacientes.

O tratamento em questão, ao contrário do que muitos possam pensar, não dizia respeito a doenças neurológicas ou psíquicas. Duchenne se utilizava desse tipo de artifício, pois era fascinado pelas expressões faciais.

Juntamente com o seu fascínio em relação à anatomia do rosto humano encontrava-se a crença de que as expressões faciais eram a linguagem da alma e que, portanto, cada gesto ou comportamento muscular era a mais pura manifestação da alma. Desta forma, para catalogar todos os tipos de expressões capazes de serem feitas pelo homem, o neurologista se utilizou de tratamentos com eletrochoque e inovou no campo médico ao utilizar a fotografia como registro dos experimentos.

Os escritos do neurologista, reunidos em sua obra intitulada "The Mechanism of Human Physiognomy", acabaram sendo utilizados por nomes renomados da Medicina e Biologia, que implementaram em seus estudos sobre a anatomia do rosto humano. Charles Darwin, por exemplo, utilizou-se do estudo de Duchenne e das fotografias de seus pacientes para compor o livro "The Expression of the Emotions in Man and Animals".

“I was recently given a bound copy of The Lady’s Magazine from 1807, originally published monthly in London, which contains stunning colour copper-plates of fashionable dress and descriptions of the garments #fashion #fashionillustration #19thcentury #dresshistory #1807 #georgianera #women The twelve copper plates, one a month, contain a high level of detail with colour applied by hand, while the descriptions illustrate the high quality materials suggested for the ensembles, such as “plain fine India muslin”, “lace”, “white satin linen”, “silver fringe”. The accessories are also lavish, with “a gold bandeau, with a pearl crescent...a drapery of fine nett (sic) spotted with gold” for a headdress in the March 1807 magazine. While the contents page for each edition suggests the magazine contains garment patterns, this bound edition is sadly missing them. Dress Historian Hilary Davidson has said this is common. What is interesting however is that the “Directions to the Binder” at the very back, does not list the patterns... suggesting, perhaps, that it was a deliberate practical or aesthetic choice?” @dresshistoryhannah

Наполеон воспользовался тактическим просчетом главнокомандующего русской армией Беннигсена, расположившего войска по обоим берегам реки Алле. Всеми имевшимися в его распоряжении силами, по ходу дела вводя в бой подходившие подкрепления, Бонапарт навалился на русские полки, оказавшиеся на левой стороне реки. Осознав свою ошибку, Беннигсен приказал отступать по наведенным мостам. Однако к ним еще нужно было пробиться через узкие улочки Фридланда. Наполеон это отлично понимал. «- Вот ваша цель, продвигайтесь, не оглядываясь по сторонам, - указал он маршалу Нею на городок. - Врежьтесь в эту плотную массу, чего бы это вам ни стоило; войдите во Фридланд, овладейте мостами и не беспокойтесь по поводу того, что будет происходить справа, слева или в тылу. Армия и я присмотрим за этим!» Ситуация для русских стала критической после того как французский генерал Сенармон, собрав 36 конных орудий, с расстояния всего 180 саженей (около 400 метров), а затем и вовсе приблизившись на 90 саженей, принялся расстреливать отступавших на картечь, перемежая ее ядрами. Это был сколь удачный, столь же и рискованный маневр. Забеспокоился даже Наполеон, приславший к Сенармону адъютанта с приказом не зарываться. «Не мешайте мне и моим канонирам, - гласил ответ генерала, - Я ручаюсь за успех». Прочитав это дерзкое донесение, Наполеон лишь произнес: « Ладно, черт с ним! – решил он - Артиллеристы люди упрямые, оставим их в покое.»

Russas é um município brasileiro do estado do Ceará. 
É conhecida como a "Terra da Laranja", "Terra de Dom Lino" e "Capital do Vale". Russas é referencial político-administrativo como sede da AmuVale (Associação dos Municípios do Vale do Jaguaribe). O município de Russas é um polo econômico com o crescente desenvolvimento de seus serviços, de expansão de suas indústrias e do agronegócio, o que ratifica sua condição de cidade-polo da região do Baixo Jaguaribe.
Originalmente chamou-se Santo Antônio do Ouvidor, depois Sítio Igreja das Russas, São Bernardo do Governador, São Bernardo de Russas e desde 1938, Russas.
Composta por caatinga arbustiva aberta, floresta caducifólia espinhosa e mata ciliar com predomínio da carnaúba.
Muitos pontos turísticos representam a cidade, como casarões, igrejas e praças.

A true newsie, delivering papers on Saturdays.

213 years strong and the coolest part is all of the old machinery is still in tact and still functional.

I was recently given a bound copy of The Lady’s Magazine from 1807, originally published monthly in London, which contains stunning colour copper-plates of fashionable dress and descriptions of the garments which I thought I’d share #fashion #fashionillustrations #19thcentury #dresshistory #1807 #georgianera #women 
The twelve copper plates, one a month, contain a high level of detail with colour applied by hand, while the descriptions illustrate the high quality materials suggested for the ensembles, such as “plain fine India muslin”, “lace”, “white satin linen”, “silver fringe”

Parisian Fashions are also described in a corresponding paragraph 
The accessories are also lavish, with “a gold bandeau, with a pearl crescent...a drapery of fine nett (sic) spotted with gold” for a headdress in the March 1807 magazine. 
While the contents page for each edition suggests the magazine contains garment patterns, this bound edition is sadly missing them. Dress Historian Hilary Davidson has said this is common. 
What is interesting however is that the “Directions to the Binder” at the very back, does not list the patterns... suggesting, perhaps, that it was a deliberate practical or aesthetic choice? @c19thdressandtextilesreframed

[ It seems that no one actually gave the “Slave Bible” a closer look. It’s not a Bible. Not really. Published in London in 1807 (and again in 1808) on behalf of the Society for the Conversion of Negro Slaves, the book bears the title Select Parts of the Holy Bible for the Use of the Negro Slaves in the British West-India Islands. Its producers were candid about its contents as partial. One might wonder, then, what rhetorical work is being done by interpreters and curators who have deemed the book a Bible—the “Slave Bible.” If it is not actually a Bible, why call it so? ]

Encore le Maroc et toujours dans la jolie ville bordée par la mer qu’est Rabat. Je vous presente ici la muraille de l’Oudayas , un ancien camp militaire du 12eme siècle, désormais inscrit au patrimoine de l’Unesco. L’ancien quartier est maintenant aménagé avec de nombreux cafés et boutiques et offre une vue directe sur l’atlantique et sur la ville voisine de Salée, située sur la rive droite de l’embouchure du Bouregreg. Les premières photos de Rabat publiée dernièrement ont d’ailleurs été prises dans l’enceinte de cet ancien quartier militaire -

.

.

從不認識到認識，從一個人變成兩個人，從陌生到熟悉，半年了👌過的好快..每天住在一起相處模式都一樣，每天一定會聽到老婆這個老婆那個😵然後什麼事一定會有對方，要幹嘛去哪裡一定會拉著對方去、除了玩電腦這件事就是不會🙄每天都要叮嚀阿肥不能玩太晚、偏偏有的時候就是很愛超過時間⌚️但..每次只要知道自己玩到超過還會跟我說下次會早點結束🔚有的時候知道明天休假，還會跟我說老婆我明天休假我今天想玩晚一點可以嗎🤓雖然說真的很討厭你玩電腦💻但一直看你塞乃，不得不還是讓你玩了😌再來吵架也很快就和好，但有的時候兩個就是很愛在那邊互嘴🥶講的很有道理、到最後還會問要和好了沒😅每天都要想著要吃什麼要吃什麼😰然後吃飽了，阿肥就會一直問，你有吃飽嗎？沒有吃飽再帶你去吃😤不得不說在一起之後直接肥死😭那個褲子好幾百件直接穿不下😑還要重買的那種🙄現在換臭阿肥在胖了，反而覺得很有成就感，半年...不長不短，還請你往後多多指教💗 @qing02_06

滔哥六個月大快樂🥳

轉眼間6個月就過去了,每天在忙亂中渡過,是我人生暫時感覺過得最快的半年。

頭一兩個月,feed on demand,對於想把時間掌控在手的媽媽來說簡直是折磨。

到第三四個月,開始在職媽媽生涯,一方面工作上要重上軌道,另一方面要習慣大部份時間只能在CCTV中看到滔哥,感覺兩面不是人。

到第五六個月,滔哥開始憧事,再沒有無理哭鬧,且經常露出笑臉,終於叫做習慣做個媽媽。

生了小孩後就像在打電動,在你以為過了一關很開心的時侯,下一關的”大佬”就會出現阻你前進。不一樣的是,這個遊戲不會GAME OVER,而你也一直遇不到那”終極大佬”

TBC…… #滔哥之日常

𓇬後追いっぽいのがでてきた？
𓇬嘘泣き覚えた
𓇬母ちゃん、やっぱり痩せてない
𓇬まだまだ完母
‏
あっとゆうまの半年！！
一気に人間っぽくなってきた🥺
‏
首が座ったのも楽になったけど腰座り少しだけどできるので、なんだかとっても楽ちんになってきた✊🏻
‏
夜泣きはまだまだあるけど🙃
いつか終わると信じて今はなんとか頑張れてる…
とりあえず1時ごろの泣きには反応薄めでトントンしたりしてる😴
‏
離乳食も始まって少しずつだけど食べるのも
じょうずになってきた𓎩𓌈
‏
GWだったので新しい食材トライできなかったけど
かぼちゃとにんじん好きみたい🥕🎃
トマトは”酸っぺぇ”って顔する😂
緑系の野菜もぱくぱくしてる！
‏
とにかく今はがむしゃらにあげて反応みて、食べる練習𓌈
‏
もう半年だし、まだ半年だし🐹
母ちゃん育休なのであと半年で仕事復帰するんだけど…
離れたくないよぉー😭😭

The fact that is also supported by evidence that most common cause of failure of the Endodontic treatment is poor coronal seal. A poor endo but with a good resto has shown better results compared to a good endo and a poor resto. The reason being the violation of the biologic goal attained with a good endo by delivering a poor post endo resto. The current evidence reveals that a bonded resto is recommended for long term sealing of the access cavity. The seal is increased by limiting the GP 2-3mm short of the orifice, and this space is being taken by the composite. Magnification is just indispensable to attain this particular objective especially in the posterior teeth.

I just received my Bach 1901B (aka Commercial Model) and my vintage Bach Stradivarius 183 flugelhorn back from Osmun Music where James Becker worked his magic on them. The commercial trumpet had a valve alignment, bell bow rounding, and resizing the tuning slides as they were really snug from the factory. The big benefit to the valve alignment is more evenness of the blow AND a more consistent pad material that holds its dimension for a longer period of time. I also switched in some brass valve guides and Osmun brass valve stems. On both horns James also gave me a set of pads to use with the original aluminum stems when I feel those would be beneficial. That way the valve alignment stays consistent! 
The flugelhorn needed a lot more love. It plays and sounds great but this is the ORIGINAL let’s call it “first draft” of the 183 flugelhorn with bottom sprung valves. Not all of the bottom sprung versions were made like this one. Note the 3rd slide to bell branch brace location, lack of 1st slide waterkey, and the position of waterkeys compared to other versions. I’ve not seen other early bottom sprung flugelhorns in this exact configuration. James has a lot of dent work to do in this horn and built spacers for for the 1st and 2nd slides as they are shorter than later horns. A 1/4” and 1/8” spacer was made for the slides to make it easier to remove and replace in the correct spot for water removal. The third slide is also shorter but actually plays better for me than the newer ones which always seem too long for notes like low G#/Ab. Then the normal blueprinting stuff was done like the valve alignment. The horn has pretty good compression for an instrument of this age so no need for a rebuild at the moment! Paleo News #183

Amber from Africa. Yes it exists! More precisely, amber from the #cenozoic (Miocene) of #ethiopia !😁
Here, a #Newspecies of fossil insect (thrip), Merothrips aithiopicus, was described!

Quoting from the abstract:
"Amber has rarely been found in Africa and only a few samples with fossil inclusions are known (Kiefert et al. 2015). The most important fossiliferous find was reported from an outcrop at the north-western Plateau of Ethiopia a decade ago, revealing diverse inclusions of arthropods, plant remains, fungi and microorganisms (Schmidt et al. 2010). Initially, this amber was classified as originating from the mid-Cretaceous. Later studies, however, have raised questions about this determination and indicated a much younger age: Cenozoic, likely Miocene (Coty et al. 2016, Perrichot et al. 2016, Perrichot et al. 2018). The contradictory—and rather controversial discussed—new dating was based on spectroscopic analyses, revised palynological data and more comprehensive palaeoentomological results showing that insect fossils mostly belong to extant families and genera. In total, Schmidt et al. (2010) reported 22 insects from eight identified orders including two specimens of Thysanoptera: “an undetermined, wingless thrips“ (obviously a larva) and a female associated with Merothripidae. A more detailed analysis of these specimens is the objective of the present study; regarding the larva, only a rough classification and description is given, as fossil larvae cannot be definitely associated with adult specimens."

【15公車-台中北屯一日遊景點推薦】
週末好天氣外出踏踏青！快跟著小編搭乘 #15公車 一起玩台中北屯吧～
（建議搭火車或客運至台中火車站 下車後步行至第一站景點遊玩）
-
📍#台中文化創意園區（從台中火車站步行約10分鐘可達）
前身為公賣局第五酒廠 2007年登錄為歷史建築 後續轉型為文創產業的推廣基地
📍#廍子公園（廍子景賢路口站）
春天時節金黃風鈴木熱情盛放 有台中最美黃金公園的美譽
📍#大坑情人橋（鄰近廍子公園）
數十條鋼纜拉出的斜張橋 猶如豎琴的造型搭配粉嫩馬卡龍色系相當吸睛
📍#185cafe（由情人橋走路10分鐘即到達）
為一間自行車旗艦店附設185cafe 綠色植栽環繞供應鬆餅、甜點與各式飲品 頂樓還有隱藏版空中花園
📍#大坑登山步道（台電東山所站）
交通便捷、景色宜人 有台中後花園的美稱 目前共有12條登山步道 9、9-1、10號步道較為平易近人
📍#老芋仔芋圓
屹立不搖的老字號冰店 選用大甲檳榔心芋頭 在地饕客、登山遊客絡繹不絕
📍#紙箱王創意園區
占地1600坪 園內展示包羅萬象的紙藝品 紙雕花園打造比薩斜塔、巴黎鐵塔等各國代表性地標
📍#太原觀光夜市(由大坑圓環站搭乘20公車至弘光復健醫院站下車)
前身是經營超過30年的東山夜市 人氣美食包括梅花肉圓、三合院古早滷味、歐豆桑蒜香烏龍豆干...等

¿Hay algo más lindo que cumplir un sueño? Bueno si, cumplir muchossss sueños!⁣
⁣
En el 2014  viaje por primera vez a Europa el cual no sólo fue un gran sueño que cumplía sino también un desafío importante, viajaba por primera vez tan lejos y por tanto tiempo sola. Fue EL despegue y dentro de ese inmenso  sueño, hubo otros más chiquitos, más modestos... algunos que incluso muchos dirán “¿soñabas con eso?” y si, sueño con muchas cosas y muy variadas... deseos de todo tipo, tamaño y color!⁣
⁣
⁣
Esta foto, que sin dudas no es la mejor, fue uno de esos sueños... “ver un cerezo en flor”... Si, soñaba con eso, nunca había visto uno (ni sin flores) y yo no les puedo explicar mi emocion ante algo tan simple y hasta común en la vida de muchos! ⁣
Creo que mi amor por Saint James Park se originó en este momento tan breve y tan  sencillo pero  en el cual me sentí como un niño en una juguetería o un parque de diversiones. ⁣
⁣
Si hay algo que me gustaría desearles a todos es que jamás pierdan la capacidad de asombro, que nunca dejen de ver el mundo con los ojos de un niño que va descubriendo diferentes universos... creo que no hay sentimiento más lindo y más genuino que este! Anímense!⁣
⁣
⁣
¿Me cuentan sus  sueños/deseos más simples? o bueno... si quieren de los más grandes también. ⁣
⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣

#懶媽媽只能一個月記錄一次

這個月又長了1顆牙，現在有18顆嘍！是因為牙齒變多，食慾也會變比較好嗎🤣 順便記錄一下平日吃完的獨照，這個月雖然只有四次，媽媽已經覺得滿足😅 雞大爺挑食部份還是一樣，但媽媽已經慢慢找到治他的辦法，希望方法能繼續延續下去~

目前除了睡不飽會非常歡難溝通以外，大致上他算是聽話的孩子~非常貼心和自動自發，至少叫了都會做！

學校生活也適應的還不錯，只是常常會問爸爸媽媽一樣的問題~
🐥：「明天放假？？」or「放假了？？」.
. .
😂😂😂😂😂😂😂 .

媽媽從沒擔心「雙子座」的適應問題，只怕雞大爺變老油條而已~

每個月都是一樣的期許~希望我們家雞大爺能夠健康平安快樂的長大❤️.

今天的便當很偷懶，把假日滷好的豬腳當主菜，煎個蛋炒個青菜就完成啦！因為雞大爺生病的時候，食慾都不太好，太多樣也是吃不完~只是.....我居然又被他傳染了😭.
.
「滷豬腳」是我覺得滷味裡面最費工的料理，因為我喜歡用慢火燉到湯汁變黏稠，難怪每次滷麥家父子倆都超喜歡，但媽媽很懶惰，只能久久滷一次喔~噗！

雞大爺🐥 2Y10M
#懶媽媽只能一個月記錄一次

因為疫情關係這一個月的假日經常都是跟媽媽在家裡或是回外公外婆家吃吃喝喝居多~食慾時好時壞，不過，這個月有比上個月吃完的次數多一些些，有七次呢~不錯不錯👏 附上吃光光的個人獨照~
#只是為什麼媽媽食慾怎麼可以一直都很好啊😅

好一陣子沒出現的腸胃炎又來了，雞大爺今早臉色慘白說他肚子好痛加上還吐個不停，嚇死我們了！立馬帶去給醫生看，果然又是『腸胃炎』~老師還特地打來關心，真的不是『武漢肺炎』啦~~也有說到這年齡的孩子很常這樣，因為太愛亂摸亂吃了，真受不了😌~~~~這個時期即使是小小的生病也都會讓人心慌慌呀！
#老師別太緊張啦
#因雞大爺腸胃炎明天便當公休一天

這個月媽媽追完韓劇【梨泰院Class】，覺得男主角朴敘俊的栗子頭也太可愛了🥰~馬上讓雞大爺也跟風一下，媽媽覺得果然很適合好可愛呀~哈哈哈

上個月03/24雞大爺老師打來說~可以開始戒尿布了，所以當天就提著三件尿濕的褲子回家，隔天就變成一件，沒想到才3天~居然就成功的戒掉白天的尿布，接下來就開始嘗試戒晚上的尿布，不知道是不是也大了的關係，畢竟都要三歲了，居然在兩週內就把白天和晚上的尿布都給戒了，雖然媽媽還是很擔心晚上會漏尿，哈哈哈~可是…媽媽才新買了兩箱拉拉褲耶~現在即使要他穿尿布都不肯，他說他長大了，不能穿尿布要穿內褲🤣

記錄一下上星期睡前的小插曲~雞大爺在床上跟麥大寶在玩樂時~
🐥邊跳邊說：『搞抱晡…搞抱晡…搞抱晡…』 因為雞大爺說的不是很清楚，加上媽媽也不是客家人，所以聽不懂他到底在說甚麼，結果麥大寶居然直接猜中！

麥大寶：「是ㄍㄧㄠˇ抱谷(客) 對不對？！」
🐥：「對~ㄍㄧㄠˇ抱谷(客)…ㄍㄧㄠˇ抱谷(客)…ㄍㄧㄠˇ抱谷(客)…哈哈哈」
媽媽：「老師是說你嗎？((已經翻白眼)) 」
🐥：「不是~~~~是”阿奇” ~~」 心想~你居然推給同學~~~雖然媽媽也知道”阿奇”很愛哭，因為上學時間有遇到幾次~噗

媽媽：「你確定老師真的不是在說你？？？」
🐥：「是”阿奇”啦！」 後來媽媽有詢問班導師，原來真的不是雞大爺耶~~老師說雞大爺在班上很乖、很配合也沒有愛哭喔！且老師也第一次聽到這個詞~說她從沒講過（因為老師也不是客家人）~~哈哈哈哈哈 那就是其他老師說的吧~不管嘍！只是媽媽覺得好好笑~
#媽媽的客語單字又新增一個

好囉~~每個月都是一樣的期許~希望我們家雞大爺能夠健康平安快樂的長大❤️ .

.

﻿
﻿
﻿
『大ちゃん ずっと一緒だよ』﻿
『大好きだよ、』﻿
『ずっと離れない』﻿
﻿
大量の粒を飲み﻿
いつの間にか用意してあったロープで自分と大ちゃんをぐるぐる巻きにする。﻿
足を絡め﻿
ギュッと抱きつき﻿

剥がされないよう﻿
絡ませあった。﻿

悲しくはない。﻿

頭の中はぼんやりし、夢をみた。﻿

﻿
2人で笑って﻿
2人で泣いて﻿
﻿
太陽のような笑顔。﻿
今にも潰れてしまいそうな儚い顔﻿

Moje kolekcjonerskie marzenie, czyli "triple dish" z serwisu White Star Line. W języku polskim nazwane byłoby "kabaretem". To naczynie, wykonane z najwyższej klasy kostnej porcelany, ręcznie zdobione, było używane jedynie w jadalnej pierwszej klasy. Identyczne wydobyto z wraku Titanica. Szacuje się, ze przetrwało ich około dwudziestu, może trzydziestu egzemplarzy.

Na zdjęciu widzimy jedynie jego fragment. Więcej o nim opowiadam na żywo w klipie nr 8 na blogowym kanale youtube Titanic - Polska Kolekcja.

Odcinek 19 (część 2) ▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️Cevdet mówi Seferowi, że w jego kieszeni znajdują się pieniądze, które jeżeli go uwolni, będą jego. Gdy bohater podchodzi, aby zabrać pieniądze, Cevdet wyjmuje z jego kieszeniu nóż, którym później go zabija. Tymczasem Ali Kemal spotyka się z Hilal oraz Azize. Siostra się cieszy, że wrócił, matka natomiast jest wściekła, że ich chciał zostawić, oraz go policzkuje. Po chwili jednak obejmuje syna i mu wybacza. Po jakimś czasie wszyscy spotykają się z Hasibe. Chłopak prosi babcię o przebaczenie, która po dłuższych namowach również mu wybacza. W międzyczasie Cevdet próbuje uciec z chaty Hasana Olmeza. Wieczorem Ali Kemal udaje się do tawerny Hacimi Halisa, w którym rozmawia z Eftalyą. Po chwili zjawia się tam również Tevfik. Kobiecie nagle pogorszył się humor oraz postanowiła zaśpiewać dla niego piosenkę. Wściekły komendant jednak prędko wychodzi. Tymczasem w pałacu Weronika rozmawia z Wasilijem. Mąż opowiada jej o tym, że w trakcie pożaru, przed wieloma laty najpierw wyjął ją, gdy się jednak cofnął po syna okazało się, że ten już nie żył. W międzyczasie do leśnego domu przychodzi Hasan Olmez. Szybko atakuje go Cevdet, który chce odciąć mu rękę. Od tyłu bohatera uderza jednak pewna dziewczyna, a ten mdleje. Leon natomiast dalej chodzi po lesie, szukając ratunku. Tymczasem do mieszkania Eftalii przychodzi Tevfik, który wyżywa się na kobiecie, ponieważ przez jej zachowanie w tawernie wszyscy mogli domyślić się, że są razem. Bohaterka po chwili zaczęła błagać mężczyznę o wybaczenie. Po jakimś czasie Tevfik przyszedł do domu Wasilija, aby przekazać fałszywe informacje na temat rzekomej śmierci wszystkich uczestników wyprawy po zaginioną broń. Wszyscy byli przerażeni tą wiadomością.

Lambay Castle. Ireland. Lambay Island lies just a mile or two off the Dublin coast. It was there, from 1905 to 1912, that architect Edwin Lutyens added to a 16th-century fort for the recently married Cecil and Maude Baring to create a remarkable building which must have been little short of idyllic.
Lambay is one of a small number of “castles” designed or remodelled by Lutyens in the pre war period to create wildly romantic and nostalgic homes including the wonderful Lindisfarne Castle on the Holy Island of Lindisfarne in Northumberland. In this evocative Country Life photo of the sitting room at Lambay sits a Windsor chair of identical design to one that I own and love. It was my studies of Lutyens as a young student that made me fall in love with country furniture. I couldn’t hope to own a Lutyen’s castle, but I could own a Windsor chair....#lambaycastle #lutyens #lutyenstrust #architect #windsorchairs #artlovers #1912 #artcollector #countrychairs #countryhouse

During the early hours of 3 June 1911 the RMS Olympic arrived in Southampton to begin preparations for her maiden voyage. As the new dock was not quite finished, the ship entered bow first. Her run from Liverpool had been successful, and her officers were pleased with the ship’s performance. Having arrived at Southampton for docking 27 hours and 45 minutes since her Liverpool departure, Olympic’s average speed over the 500 mile distance was a moderate 18 knots.

Como el nuevo muelle no estaba del todo terminado, el barco entró en proa. Su recorrido desde Liverpool había sido exitosa, y sus oficiales estaban satisfechos con el rendimiento del barco. Odcinek 18 ▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️ Azize udaje się pod dom Eftalii. Zastaje tam kobietę, oraz prosi, aby powiedziała, co wie na temat Cevdeta. Ta jednak nie chce nic mówić bohaterce, ponieważ Azize wcześniej nie chciała jej słuchać. Ali Kemal zostaje w Izmirze, ponieważ kiedy chciał wsiąść na statek oraz odpłynąć, zatrzymali go żołnierze wysłani przez Cevdeta. Postanowił zatem przyjąć ofertę lichwiarza Steinera - będzie dla niego pracował. Tymczasem Tevfik dopatruje zleconego przez niego remontu domu Azize, który wcześniej spłonął w pożarze. Cevdet natomiast cały czas przebywa porwany w leśnym domku Hasana Olmeza. W międzyczasie Leon przebudził się po tym, jak mąż Azize go ogłuszył.
Chłopak zaczął chodzić po lesie, aby szukać ratunku, natomiast gdy zauważyli go ludzie mordercy-partyzanta, szybko zaczął uciekać. Niestety bohater został postrzelony oraz stracił przytomnośc. Po upływie kilku godzin ponownie się obudził, po czym podsłuchał rozmowę, z której wynikało, że wszyscy uczestnicy wyprawy nie żyją, a ich ciała zostały wrzucone do rzeki.

For information about David Stewart Dawson (1849-1932), founder of Stewart Dawson & Co., retail goldsmiths, jewellers, &c., in Great Britain, Australia and New Zealand, see Wikipedia https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_Stewart_Dawson.
+
David Stewart Dawson's son, Percy Stewart Dawson (1888-1947) was married to Thelma Victoria Maud Bell Morton (6 September 1890 – 29 June 1966), better known as the actress and singer, Thelma Raye. Although the couple had already had a daughter, Dawn, born at Bournemouth in England on 1 April 1913, they were not wed until 21 March 1917. The marriage foundered, however, and in March 1918 Miss Raye returned to London. During 1919 she was on a U.K. tour as the lead in Cosmo Hamilton’s play, Scandal. It was at about this time that she met the actor Ronald Colman (1891-1958); they were married on 18 September 1920. Frustrated by his inability to make headway with his career, Colman left England for New York less than a month later followed by Thelma. There is little doubt that Colman’s steeply rising success as a Hollywood star soon put an intolerable strain on this marriage. The couple publicly acknowledged a breakdown in their relationship by early 1926 and although separated they did not formally split for another eight years.

Odcinek 19 ▪️▪️▪️▪️▪️ Cevdet cały czas jest przetrzymywany przez Hasana Olmeza. Jego pomocnik - Sefer cały czas gardzi bohaterem oraz wyżywa się na nim przez to, że przeszedł on na stronę Greków. Tymczasem Ali Kemal szuka nowego stroju w sklepie Eleni. Do przyjaciółki przychodzi również Yıldız, która załamana mówi o tym, że Azize chce wydać ją za ordynatora pobliskiego szpitala. Zszokowany brat bohaterki wyskakuje z przebieralni. Dziewczyna ucieszyła się na widok brata, ponieważ myślała, że ten wyjechał. Zdziwiła się również, że bohater przymierzał drogie ubrania. W międzyczasie amerykański redaktor przeprowadza wywiad z Andreasem. Bohater opowiada o tym, jak w żołnierze w Menemenie zaatakowali dom, w którym mieszkała staruszka z wnuczką. Żołnierz Marco stwierdził, że kobiecie, która próbowała ratować dziewczynkę połamie kości nawet bez broni, ponieważ stare kości łatwo się łamią. Później po wyjściu z domu znaleźli jej wnuczkę na drzewie. Postanowili, że ten, który ją złapie, będzie miał ją dla siebie. Przerażona Hilal, która była przy tej rozmowie nie mogła tego słuchać i szybko wybiegła z pokoju. Tymczasem Ali Kemal zabrał Yıldız do drogiej restauracji, w której rozmawiali na temat jej przyszłych zaręczyn. Po długiej rozmowie bohater obiecuje siostrze, że jeżeli ta nie chce wychodzić za ordynatora, to on się na te zaręczyny nie zgodzi. W międzyczasie Weronika przychodzi do Hasibe. Pyta się kobiety, jak to jest myśleć, że w własne dziecko nie żyje. Bohaterka odpowiada, że jest bardzo ciężko w to uwierzyć. Opowiada również historię o tym, że w wieku piętnastu lat urodziła pierwsze dziecko. Kiedy Hasibe była w ciąży z Cevdetem, to ono zachorowało. Przez to, że wszyscy bali się o to, że drugie dziecko kobiety zarazi się tą chorobą, Hasibe nie mogła ostatni raz przytulić swojego syna. Starszy brat Cevdeta, który miał na imię Ali Kemal, zmarł, a na jego cześć przybrany syn głównego bohatera otrzymał jego imię. Tymczasem Tevfik przyszedł do Hasana Olmeza by upewnić się, że ten zabije Cevdeta. Morderca powiedział, że wywiąże się z umowy pod warunkiem, że komendant zapłaci więcej.

QUANDO VOLTAR!🇮🇹
O elenco do Palmeiras não tem uma definição para voltar a usar a Academia de Futebol, mas o Núcleo de Saúde e Performance já discute os procedimentos que serão tomados para o trabalho com os jogadores.

O tema foi debatido por profissionais da área no primeiro evento do 2º Congresso Palmeiras de Ciência no Futebol. O trabalho de prevenção de futuras lesões inclui novos testes cardiológicos, em parceria com o Hospital Sírio Libanês, por causa da pandemia do novo coronavírus.
.
.
– Sabemos que para os atletas que testarem positivo em algum momento, temos que pesquisar se houve danos cardiológicos, renais, hepáticos, porque sabemos que a Covid tem essa característica de alguns danos celulares. Todos os nossos atletas, em convênio com o Sírio, serão novamente testados na parte cardiológica. Vamos verificar os déficits das condições anteriores para ter um trabalho específico nesse retorno, de forma que consigamos prevenir lesões – afirmou Daniel Gonçalves, coordenador científico do Verdão.

Na Europa, a Alemanha foi o primeiro país a voltar com o campeonato entre as principais ligas do continente. Nas seis primeiras partidas, porém, oito atletas sofreram lesões, ainda em maio.

Je vous présente "14-14", il a été écrit par Silène Edgar et Paul Besoin, ce livre vient de l'édition Castelmore.
. 
Adrien et Hadrien ont treize ans et habitent tous les deux en Picardie. Ils ont les mêmes préoccupations : l'école, la famille, les filles…  Une seule chose les sépare: Adrien vit en 2014 et Hadrien en 1914. Grâce à une boîte aux lettres mystérieuse, les deux adolescents vont s'échanger du courrier et devenir amis. Mais la Grande Guerre est sur le point d'éclater pour Hadrien et leur correspondance pourrait bien s'interrompre de façon dramatique…
. 
Wouah! Ce livre je l'ai dévoré rapidement en trois soir et il avait une histoire très intéressante. J'ai aimé suivre l'histoire de Adrien et Hadrien. Je le recommande!
. 
Merci beaucoup à @livres_comme_lair de m'avoir prêté cette merveille.
.

FORÇA JEAN!🇮🇹
O volante Jean, do Cruzeiro, está com coronavírus. O jogador testou positivo na nova série de testes feitas pelo clube para a detecção da Covid-19 entre atletas, funcionários e comissão.

O Cruzeiro informou que Jean está assintomático, foi afastado das atividades de hoje na Toca da Raposa 2 e vem adotando as orientações de isolamento social em sua residência, em Belo Horizonte.

Nehéz írni ma, főleg közhelymentesen. Sokaknak csak egy szókapcsolat a "trianoni békeszerződés". De diktátum, nem szerződés, mert abba mindegyik fél beleegyezik, aláírja azt. Hogy is lehetne béke - az egyik legszebb szavunkat nem szabadna ezzel egy lapon emlegetni. A versaillesi palota Trianon terme pedig örökre megpecsételődött. Ugyanúgy, mint az, aki határokon kívül-vagy belül rekedt. Már senki sem él, aki átélte a csonkítást, de annyira családjainkba, kollektív nemzettudatunkba ivódott június negyedike! Annyira a gyász különböző fázisaiban vagyunk, és ezt nem gyógyítja meg még pár emberöltő után sem az, ha átnevezzük nemzeti összetartozás napjává. Emlékeznünk kell! Enélkül azokat az őseinket tagadnánk meg, akik akaratlanul ott harcoltak a frontvonalban, akiket elhurcoltak, akik fogságba estek, akik otthon próbáltak túlélni. Most pedig beszéljenek a számok: a Magyar Királyság veszteségei az első világháborúban: 661 ezer hősi halott, 730 ezer sebesült, 730 ezer hadifogoly. Magyarország a trianoni békediktátum értelmében 191 735 négyzetkilométert veszített el. Elcsatoltak 10 781 773 lakost és 3 727 205 magyar idegen uralom alá került. 4 241 gyárból 2 166-ot elvettek. 19 723 kilométer vasútvonalból csak 8 364 kilométer maradt. Magyarország elvesztette 92 városát, út-és csatornahálózatának 80 százalékát. Odalett minden só-, ezüst- és aranybánya. Réz-, mangán- és higanykészlet nélkül maradt. Másé lett az olajkutak többsége. Idegen kézbe került a fenyőerdők 97, a lombhullató erdők 85 és tölgyesek 68 százaléka. Magyarország nemzeti vagyona az 1914 előttinek a 38 százalékára zsugorodott 1920-ra. #trianon #trianon100 #1914 #1920 #nemzetiösszetartozásnapja #június4

Jan. 6-7, 2020﻿
—  新年花東之旅 —﻿
﻿
這次拜訪了兩大祕境：竹林山竹林湖與都歷海灘﻿
﻿
都歷海灘在平日也是祕境，﻿
從頭到尾只遇到兩組遊客，﻿
沙子很細踩起來舒服，﻿
最大的特色是海浪打起來的時候，﻿
沙子表面會留下一些水分，﻿
形成一片鏡子，可以反射景物，﻿
尤其人站在上面真的完全反射，﻿
不過大浪來襲時鏡子會先消失，﻿
再慢慢顯現出鏡子的功能，﻿
非常適合放鬆發呆。﻿
﻿

Day 18, 81.6km, 大晴

台東到花蓮186km，本來我以為弱弱的我們會分3天來騎，結果昨天超乎預期的100公里後，今天只剩下70多公里就可以到花蓮市了。
當然反骨的我是不會照著環島1號線沿著台9線來騎，到了瑞穗後就騎進單車店老闆推薦的花蓮193縣道。和傳統的台9線不同的是，193縣道沿途沒有城鎮，看到的都是一片片的農耕地，黃梨園，檳榔樹，還有原住民部落。
到了太巴塱社區，還會看到每家每戶外面都一定有木雕裝飾，沿途看到的老人都以阿美族語在交談，和我平時身處的台灣有點不一樣。
雖然193縣道會多走大概10公里路，也多爬幾段坡，但是我覺得比起台9線被大卡車超過的感覺更輕鬆了。
今天時間充足，當我們走到花蓮大橋時，太陽也還沒下山，所以今天終於不用夜騎了。
照著我們計畫的路程，我們大概只剩下3天就能回到台北了。當然來到東部，我們還是會選擇多留花蓮一天，明天又是在花蓮周邊吃吃喝喝咯

Jan. 6-7, 2020﻿
—  新年花東之旅 —﻿
﻿
這次拜訪了兩大祕境：竹林山竹林湖與都歷海灘﻿
這個竹林山不是林口的，而是玉里的竹林山，﻿
因為都在平日，抵達竹林湖的時候沒其他遊客，﻿
就連結束下山的時候也沒遇到上山拜訪的人，﻿
竹林湖除祕境外，就是隔壁養得三隻德國狼犬。﻿
﻿
即將抵達目的地轉彎的一剎那，被狗嚇到，﻿
因為牠躺在路中央，但沒有對我叫，﻿
而是站起身，然後往前衝幾步再回頭看我，﻿
我就也繼續往前走，喔～牠居然帶我去找湖欸，﻿
後來發現其實有3隻，聰明到知道我是來看湖，﻿
而不是來亂的，牠站起來跟摩托車一樣高大，﻿
我真的一度以為我會變成牠們的下午茶，﻿
其實牠們非常溫馴給摸，下山也要湊一下熱鬧，﻿
歡送你下山哈哈哈。﻿

May 29,2020

七星潭半月形海灣後方，有座80多年歷史的2618號保安林，北起三棧溪出海口，向南延伸至德燕漁場聚落，涵蓋狹長的七星潭林帶。

1938年，為了阻擋太平洋季節強風、風砂、鹽、潮水的侵襲、保護聚落安全，日本政府將七星潭沿岸的森林編定為保安林，延續至今。林帶蜿蜒貫穿加灣與康樂聚落，在林蔭中沿著月牙海灣騎著單車，欣賞各種海岸動植物與大海美景，是另類的消暑享受。

完成機車環島之旅！
扣除玩耍行程，慢慢騎也繞完一圈了。
從來不騎遠路的我、超過八公里絕對是搭車的我，自己繞完了將近一千公里路程，也體驗到騎車樂趣。

單獨旅遊跟有旅伴截然不同，總是臨時起意的我，向來只有對自己才敢任性出發的勇氣。

三年前因為很棒的旅伴（一定要提100次真的很棒😋），
一起在空巴管制區為遠遠的梅花塗裝歡呼、為A380第一次試車的cockpit view影片抽氣、買一大堆路人不懂的飛行飄帶、在monoprix 掃貨亞洲貴得要命的主婦用品(買到要搭下一班列車)、
看好美的冰河、一起漫步在美麗的小鎮市集、
吃一隻廣場上的彩虹玫瑰冰淇淋、在起司餐廳裡面刮下剛融下的整塊起司再塗上salami大口吞下，
然後跟法國店員說：Oui! Mademoiselle, bien sur. J’ai toujour vingt ans.
我還拖拉到要出發去瑞士時才把在荷蘭寫的明信片寄給自己🤣

因為這個契機，重新對擁有旅伴這件事憧憬，
隔年也再次嘗試了姐妹出遊，在釜山跟曼谷都是每天水晶晶偶爾勞晶晶。

隨後進入了倦怠期，很長一段時間，連帶家人旅行都只剩下承諾的份量，
只是想看家人的笑容，當然過程中不斷被陽光給療癒。
那一年自己又獨自去了趟曼谷跟清邁假期，
只是找不到旅行的熱情。
（但遇到老朋友的那晚仍然非常非常快樂！

2019下半年開始，
很想要找個可以一起看飛機的、最好有點浪漫可以一起路邊臨停為美景屏息的旅伴。
（因為我就是很容易被有的沒的給吸引走的傻瓜旅人類型🤣）
不用有壓力、各走各的也沒問題，可以分享今天走了什麼點，一起吃頓飯、share housing的那種。
特別是自己一個人在東京街頭迷路第一百次的時候很有感😂！
喝到一杯很厲害的咖啡，為他的香氣跟層次深深感動時，
點開了咖啡朋友的對話窗、傳了評價跟照片過去，又發個限時動態，
可是總是不如親臨現場一起共享的那種亢奮。

2020年，原本約了許多約。
去road trip、去air show、去姐妹單身之旅、去追飛機。
因為這波疫情，我前面一個多月超級低潮，
經濟壓力好像變成了everything壓在自己身上。
直到終於開始扭轉自己心態的時候，某些狀態也變了。
於是我再次打包行李、走上單獨旅行。
這一次，告訴自己出發就是了。

一萬個顧慮都是別人給的，獨自在海外闖蕩幾回也好好回家的自己，除了運氣更因為我一直擁有警覺與彈性不是嗎？
問了環島過的人幾個問題，借了裝備、再排個住宿順序，
確認都準備好、旅費像乳溝一樣擠出來了，竟然在出發前興奮地睡不著。
半夜乾脆隨意像網路分享的YouTuber一樣做了張環島中牌子，想著在台灣有什麼問題都能解決，車子一發就出門了。

然後昨天下午抵達後，回家第一件事依然是unpacking, laundry, couched🤣。
陷在沙發裡聽洗衣機運轉著，傳訊息給幾個對話框說我到家了！
然後打給哈尼，好好聊了對接下來生活的各種不知所措，
唯一知道的只有自己要搬家到哪裡，然後一起嘆好多氣。
哈尼說，其實妳可以不用離開的。
我說，是呀！可是我需要改變。

桌上還散著待整理的東西、一邊清一邊提筆準備寫清單，但還是忍不住打開手機看起了飛機✈️。 今天早上看到，某個對話框回訊問，旅行有什麼感想嗎？
打到這邊想了想，
可能是找回獨自旅行的快樂吧！
（而且意外發現人家的旅人運原來不是只有在海外旺，國內也堪用🤣。
很謝謝每一站照顧我的朋友，無論新的舊的錯身而過的。

想起某個下午停好車，走在路邊準備吃飯時、還被一台焦急的小客車停下問，
小姐！你在環島嗎？這個方向不對唷～
忍不住笑了。

還是想要一個可以並肩而行的旅伴，走遍世界的許多角落。
不過，在那之前我想我可以再次自己出發了！
先去一些沒那麼容易迷路的地方吧🤣🤣🤣 #公路之旅

Yosifu 優席夫，旅英畫家，出身台灣花蓮縣玉里鎮的馬泰林村。目前定居英國愛丁堡，長期在歐洲以台灣原住民為題推動台灣文化發展，也是首位躍上國際舞台的阿美族當代藝術家。

#花蓮 #最美公路 #193縣道 #花東縱谷 #環島旅行  #day1 
這次環島完全沒停景點，因沿路的美景已經夠吸引我。

193線道，是花蓮的經典之路，北起七星潭，南端到玉里。一路景色多變，山、海、一望無際的稻田，和壯麗的縱谷，通通飽覽！

北段為海岸線路段，路旁緊依蔚藍的太平洋，可遠眺完整的海平面；路上還會經過幾處小漁村。

中段為山路，沿著海岸山脈而行，可從高處遠眺整個花東縱谷，沿路有許多小部落，及原始古道的痕跡

南段為一望無際的稻田路，陽光灑落，鄉村樸實的味道撲鼻而來，穿越一間又一間的矮房，和田中的稻浪。

這裡有一個有名部落叫「太巴塱」，意思就是「富田之地」。 而著名的金針花山「六十石山」和「赤柯山」，就位於這條路上的岔支。

最南端來到的玉里，就一定要吃「玉里麵」和「玉里臭豆腐」，犒賞自己越過整個花蓮縱谷。

193縣道也是人生必騎的自行車路線，摩托車的速度終究還是太快了，決定下次租一台腳踏車，再重新細細騎過一次.. 有誰要跟？ 
補充：IG前幾張都是193縣道沿路拍的照片

Little Richard is the founding father of rock & roll. He completely changed the musical trajectory of the 1950s and beyond. Without him, there would be no Beatles, no Elton John, no Kinks, no Elvis Costello, no Rolling Stones, no Scorpions, and no CCR. Without him, there is no rock music. Period. There is no Guns’n’Roses, Nirvana, or Ramones. Without him, there is no me. He was a trailblazer and a genius, and he was a quiet civil rights pioneer whose concerts helped push culture past segregation. He died just last month, and he died never being considered equal to the myriad white artists he influenced over the past 60+ years. 🎹 🎸🙏

This is Dorothy Counts-Scoggins who at age 15 became the first African-American female to enroll at Harry Harding High School, a previously all white school in Charlotte, North Carolina in 1957. After four days of harassment that threatened her safety, her parents forced her to withdraw from the school. (#swipe 👈🏽)
⠀
Dorothy, whose nickname was Dot, was dropped off on her first day of school by her father Herman Counts, along with their family friend Edwin Thompkins. As their car was blocked from going closer to the front entrance, Edwin offered to escort Counts to the front of the school while her father parked the car. As Counts got out of the car to head down the hill, her father told her: "Hold your head high." The harassment started when the wife of John Z. Warlick, an officer of the White Citizen Council, urged the boys to "keep her out" and at the same time, implored the girls to spit on her, saying: "Spit on her, girls, spit on her." Counts walked by without reacting, but told the press later that many people threw rocks at her—most of which landed in front of her feet—and that students formed walls but parted ways at the last minute to allow her to walk past.
⠀
Counts fell ill the following day. With a fever and aching throat, she stayed home from school for the next two days, but had hoped to start the next week better. On her first day, she had befriended two white female students and hoped their friendship would lessen the stress of starting a new school. As she arrived the following week on Monday, the girls told her they could not be friends with her anymore due to them enduring their own harassment while she was absent, including eggs being thrown at them. A few days later on Wednesday, Counts requested to go home for lunch after a group of boys spit in her food the previous day. When she returned that afternoon with her brother, a bystander threw something at their car and shattered the back window. The following day, a week after her first arrival, her parents pulled her from Harding High. -#repost .

.

Grace vient de remporter l’Oscar de la meilleure actrice pour son rôle dans « Une fille de la province » (1954). Son nouveau statut de célébrité internationale en parallèle de son aura bourgeois lui vaut l’attention du Prince Rainier III.

C’est alors durant son séjour au Festival de Cannes en tant qu’invitée que le souverain monégasque lui fait la cour. Le duo s’éprend l’un de l’autre. Ils annonceront leur mariage un an plus tard.

L’icône du cinéma changera alors radicalement de vie en devenant la nouvelle Princesse de Monaco. Ses styles influenceront des milliers d’adulatrices.

This is the beautiful model, China (pronounced Chee-na) Machado. Born in Shanghai to a Chinese mother and Portuguese father, she moved to Paris and began modelling in 1958. At the time she was described as ‘exotic’, and after much resistance from the publisher of Harper’s Bazaar at risk of losing subscriptions, became the first non-white model to feature in an American fashion magazine, in 1959. When modelling for American designer Oleg Cassini, Southern buyers refused to purchase any design worn by her “because she’s black!”, which evidently she was not. She just wasn’t Caucasian. That alone is an indication of how warped a perception of anything non-white can become in the industry. You may read stories like this and think how glad you are that this is in the past. But it is not. It is just as relevant today as it was then. I celebrate the work of China and the indelible legacy she has left 💙 #chinamachado

客人除了喜歡餐點也喜歡洋房🏡

我們費工耗時打掉了圍牆、移走電線桿、調整變電箱的位置，整修的過程歷經近一年。還遇到連兩週的大雨，毀損了一樓的壁紙，連寶貴的櫥櫃都差點不保。

老屋有很多狀況是要跟時間賽跑🏃‍♀️的，每當客人表達了對洋房的喜歡及美味💕，都是我們最開心🥳的時候。

那些埋頭努力滴下的汗水💦還有開店的辛苦也就值得了❤️ 真的謝謝每個喜歡洋房的你/妳

1958 古典洋房
位於台南市東區長榮中學旁巷弄內
穿越彎曲小徑後從轉角轉出
肅立眼前的 是棟唯美老式洋房

店內以南洋風味餐點為主
主餐均含湯品、飲品、茶凍
甜點部分也可以加購升級成奶酪哦！

泰式打拋豬特別採用泰國香米製作 
香氣四溢卻不會太嗆辣
搭配有機紅心蛋 清爽可口

青檸打拋義大利麵
義式料理結合南洋風味
酸甜滋味在嘴裡化開

越南滴漏煉乳咖啡 
市面上較少看到 
等待上層咖啡滴完之後和煉乳攪拌
不會太甜膩 頗具特色風味

附餐甜點是清爽美味的茶凍
也可以加銅板價換購成芝麻鮮奶酪
滿滿的芝麻味與鮮奶融入製作
香濃滑順不膩口！

清幽的環境 美味的餐點
喜歡復古氛圍的朋友可以走訪一遭！

因著防疫，我們的來客確實受到了影響。

看著台南各家餐飲同業開始推出外賣🥡，我們也曾掙扎著是否這麼做。

目前無法的理由是，我們實在不忍在這時有更多的垃圾製造讓🌍地球負擔，另外則是擔心影響現場的來客。我們重視每個來到的客人，即使是一個人用餐。

更重要的是夥伴的出餐模式的改變調整，若無法兼顧滿足現場客人及外帶的客人的用餐品質。我們是無法貿然推行的。

雖然接到好幾通打來要外帶的電話☎️，但很抱歉，我們目前還是沒辦法推出。但我們會繼續思考如何兼顧環保與新鮮美味的外帶方式。

新鮮、現製、美味，並減少地球🌍的負擔一直是我們的宗旨。當然我們做出這樣的決定也代表著，冒著虧損的風險，但我們會努力💪堅持下去。

今天晚上位置還很多，您可以安心來店用餐🍴。 桌間也都有適當的距離及分隔。

【 1958古典洋房 】
走進老洋房‧啜飲懷舊記憶
-
✨1958是老洋房的出生年份，歲月流逝60個年頭過去了，經過店主的堅持與修復，保留了洋房最美的樣子，洋房的故事就此再度展開新的篇章…
-
🏡轉進長榮路巷弄中，很難不被這棟古典洋房吸引目光，深淺褐色的馬賽克磚與小口磚包圍著整棟建築，白色Y字形鐵窗花沿著二樓陽台屹立著，陽光灑下時，每一片磁磚都閃耀獨特的光彩…
-
🏡推門而入，循著地板墨綠色不規則磁磚走至杏色圓形花磚，先是驚嘆保存良好的復古的木櫥與拱門雕花，後則為天花板與牆面的圓弧形交界讚嘆，具餐廳店主表示，眼前所見的老洋房大部分為原始模樣再經過店主的細心修復後呈現，加上金色吊燈、木製桌椅、白紗窗簾與植栽，店裡飄漾著華麗復古又帶有點南洋殖民的慵懶閒適氣息…
-
🍽餐點皆為套餐，附湯、80元飲品、甜點…
#泰式打拋豬飯豪華增量版  #280NT
🍛店裡人氣餐點之一，鹹香帶有辣度的豬肉末，香料香氣明亮，搭配半熟蛋液與泰國香米，店主調整為適合台灣人的口味，溫暖脾胃，令人胃口大開…
適合食量較大者，除了肉、菜量增加外，還可以免費續飯一次
-
#香煎雞腿排蔬食麵包  #340NT
🥘外皮煎得酥脆內裡軟嫩多汁的雞腿排，搭配營養新鮮的生菜、炒蛋與手工黑糖麥片，伴著鬆軟的小圓麵包，療癒身體一週的疲憊….
-

不知道是不是因為陰天，最擁擠的假日午間有些悠閒。那也很好，客人會得到更多有品質的用餐時光，我們也很開心🥳

想吃個午餐或晚起的餐，都歡迎過來。目前都有位置❤️😘 🔺🔺🔺然後有個非常重要的事項要提醒第一次來的客人。

店內側邊我們的3格停車格🅿️，採顧客隨到隨停，不予保留，停🈵️的話，請利用長榮路上的▶️▶️▶️「德化」停車場，停好走過來洋房🏡只需要1分鐘路程。就這麼1分鐘，一點都不困難。

我們做了眾多告示且不厭其煩說明，圍牆外⛔️➡️「整排」都是⚠️私人停車格。

台南的小巷是不可能有任人停放的車位。

當您貪圖自己的便利的同時，附近的鄰居跟店家還有其他遵守規則的客人，都要承受您造成影響。（鄰居每每遇到這樣的狀況，進店情緒不佳、言語大聲找亂停車的車主，我們店家困擾且影響其他用餐的客人）

以上是少例，九成九的客人都有禮貌且遵守停車的規範，負責地將愛車🚗停在「合法」停車場及停車格。

結論：

來用餐請遵守交通規則，把車停在停車場🅿️，遵守店家的提醒（預約的客人我們都會傳停車場的提醒），請當個尊重自己與他人的好公民！

讓人吃完還會想念的1958
1.打拋豬選大份量的可免費續飯一次，可調整辣度
2.南洋咖喱雞飯，雞肉好嫩，微辣好下飯

6.店員還是美麗氣質有夠溫柔的0ㄗ👍👍👍服務👍👍👍
7.吸管還是環保吸管有夠加分！希望大家都能減少使用塑膠吸管～～

#泰式打拋豬飯🐷🍳 #台南美食

這款滴漏咖啡金杯有一個旅行的故事。

在洋房還沒開始營業前，一個偶然的機會去到河內🇻🇳。走在著名的17街上，遇到了整排販售越南咖啡豆的店家。

走遍了整條街才買到了這稀少的滴漏金杯，百分之九十九在台灣的店家使用的都是白鐵跟銀色器具。

很巧合的是賣給我們的店主人，竟然學過中文，完全沒有溝通上的問題。後來有很多客人詢問是否有販售，很遺憾地我們只有店內的這幾組，實在無法販售。連店內夥伴都想要購買😂，可是真的沒有庫存可販售。

也許未來有機會回去河內，再購置一些回來給喜愛這款金色滴漏杯款的客人們。

另外，我們的越南咖啡是完全道地的味道，跟義式花式或單品咖啡是完全不同的味道。

沒有喝過的客人建議要加煉乳，會喝到巧克力及奶油混合煉乳的味道。因為越南咖啡豆製程深烘焙並加入奶油烘拌製成。

我們不是台南第一家販售越南滴漏咖啡的店家，有家食物也很美味同樣販售滴漏咖啡的店家也悄悄地改成義式咖啡粉滴漏，讓我們覺得甚為可惜。

這個咖啡味道與台灣人習慣的義式咖啡相當不同，但來到洋房絕對🏡可以體驗道地的🇻🇳越南滴漏咖啡風味，是在其他地方很困難找到的。歡迎您來體驗一番❤️ 今天又是一陣忙碌的節奏，目前外場人手不足，若有招待不週處，還請客人包涵，小店感激不盡🙇‍♀️ #

4 июня 1969 по-летнему одетый 18-летний кубинец Армандо Сокаррас Рамирес подобрался к готовящемуся взлететь самолету DC-8 и привязал себя к стойке шасси. Полет проходил на высоте 8-9 километров при температуре воздуха -40°. Через несколько часов самолет приземлился в Мадриде, там Рамиреса обнаружили и, в коматозном состоянии, отправили в больницу. Медики сказали, что он не замерз насмерть, потому что впал в анабиоз. А потом оттаял как лягушка весной.
На фото техник авиакомпании Air Canada показывает, где именно во время полета сидел кубинский беглец.
Сей трюк с тех пор многие пытались повторить, но удавался он лишь в первой части, без продолжения после слов "замерз насмерть".
Физика, бессердечная ты сука.
Ну, за развитие авиатуризма!

Jean Ferrat. Ma France. 1969.
.
C’était l’album que l’on écoutait en K7 dans la voiture lorsque nous partions en vacances en famille. Enfin, justement, ma mère n’avait pas enregistré toutes les chansons du disque. Bien sûr, on écoutait Ma France qui a mes yeux reste l’une des plus belles chansons de Ferrat. Une chanson certes éminemment politique mais rien de plus beau qu’une chanson politique réussie quand elle chante aussi bien les louanges d’un pays, de ses paysages, de son histoire et de ses artistes. Une chanson qui sera interdite pendant deux ans... avant d’être diffusée à la télé par Yves Mourousi !
« Picasso tient le monde au bout de sa palette » Aurait-il su peindre la lumière éclatante de La matinée que chante aussi dans ce disque Jean Ferrait avec sa compagne Christine Sèvres ? Un autre très beau morceau sur l’espoir des jours meilleurs.
Il faut également passer par la case Aragon avec Les poètes. Magnifique ! Jean Ferrat s’amuse de la carrière des chanteurs amenés à disparaître et se ringardiser avec l’amusant L’idole à papa dans lequel il reprend des passages de ses anciennes chansons en imitant la voix de Tino Rossi.
Enfin dans les autres morceaux à retenir de ce disque on peut ajouter Au printemps de quoi rêvais-tu ? qui raconte le vent de liberté engendré par Mai 68... sans pour autant faire preuve de naïveté.
Bref cinq chansons particulièrement réussies qui éclipsent sûrement le reste de l’album moins inspiré en tout cas moins inspirant.
A réécouter : Au printemps de quoi rêvais-tu ?

Me lembro perfeitamente do dia que a minha cliente perguntou se ela poderia ter um sofá vermelho na sala. E eu respondi que sim 🤩 O meu trabalho é sem regras! Costumo dizer que o meu papel é de direcioná-los ao encontro deles próprios, interpretar o seus desejos e materializar no espaço as suas personalidades nos termos da estética, da sensação e da função, para que assim, eles se sintam pertencentes, confortáveis e seguros. 
Mas foi a primeira vez que alguém citou sobre usar a cor vermelha na decoração residencial... E no princípio era o vermelho. Foi a primeira cor que o homem batizou, é a denominação cromática mais antiga do mundo! Além de ser uma cor que homens e mulheres gostam igualmente.

Mas ainda é um cor pouco utilizada nas nossas casas, talvez por ser muito aplicada em restaurantes e na publicidade!  E quando tudo começa a ficar colorido demais, a primeira cor que incomoda é o vermelho. O vermelho é a cor entre as cores. O vermelho é,de modo geral, a cor dos extrovertidos. O vermelho não tem como ficar em segundo plano.! Vermelho é a cor simbólica de todas as atividades que exigem mais paixão do que compreensão!

Que tal experimentar novas composições de cor para extrair a positividade que o vermelho pode te oferecer?

b.b.king, completely well, 1969

abc'nin blues yapımlari icin olusturduğu ve altmiş sonlarinda ve yetmislerin ilk yarisinda bayaği etkin olan yavru etiketi bluesway'dan atalarımiza ulasan completely well'i 1969'un basarili blues uzuncalarları arasına katmak mümkün elbette. 
b.b.king 16 eylül 1925 itta, mississippi dogumlu. gitarcı 14 mayıs 2015'te öldüğunde ardında dev bir miras birakmış. all music guide'a bakacak olursak king of the blues (1960), live at the regal (1965), john henry (1993) en kayda deger olanlari.

b.b.king'i tıfılllar eric clapton leşi ve u2 molozlarıyla caldıgı icin efsanelesmiş sansalar da kıralın guney eyaletlerinde, ozellikle. memphis'te edindigi deneyim, kuzeni bukka white'in yaninda aldigi eğitim cok onemli. 
completely well king'in ses getirmiş bir otuzüçlügu, özellikle yetmislerde nerdeyse tum bluescuların yorumladıgı the thrill is gone ile tanınıyor öncelikle.

elektrikli gitarı ustalikla konusturan, parcaları kudretle soyleyen king'in yaninda klavyelileri paul harris, ritim gitari hugh mccracken, basgitarı gerald jemmott, davulu herbie lovelle calmıs. zaman zaman kullanilan uflemeli ve yaylilar duzenlemelerini ise bert de coteaux yapmış. 
kayitlar 1969'da the hit factory'de yapilmiş.

completely well'in king'in müzik yasantisindaki onemi kendisini en sonunda tahta oturtmasiyla, coktan hak ettigi üne kavusturmasiyla iliskili. oyle diyor amg'deki tanitim yazisinda cub koda!

uzuncalarda 9 parca yer aliyor. alti tanesinde king'in imzası var. tum parcalar esinle icra edilmis. you're mean, the thrill is gone ve confessin' the blues sanki en guclü olanları. 😃😎😃 #bbking #completelywell #1969

June 2nd was the 50th anniversary of Bruce McLaren’s passing at the young age of 32. He was testing an M8D McLaren race car (pictured in the screen saver)Sussex England June 2nd, 1970. 
His character & the stories told of him are that of legends. That McLaren spirit & design and the 2015 Geneva Auto show inspired our McLaren Art Project.

PASSION // CONTEMPORAIN ❤️
Le nouveau roman de Douglas Kennedy sort aujourd'hui et quel roman !
Isabelle, l'après midi est peut-être le roman le plus doux, sensuel et intime que l'auteur a pu écrire. ▪️Sam rencontre Isabelle un soir en 70 à Paris. Coup de foudre. Pendant 30 ans, ils vont vivres une relation parallèle à leur vie respective. L'un à New York, l'autre à Paris.
▪️Je suis une lectrice qui ne pleure pas. Aussi étrange que cela puisse paraître, je suis très sensible, mais les romans ne me donne jamais la larme. Pourtant, j'ai fini le roman en m'effondrant. Parce que Douglas Kennedy réussi à écrire l'âme humaine avant tant de justesse que j'ai eu l'impression qu'il écrivait pour moi. Sam et Isabelle, c'est mon homme et moi. Cette sensation profonde de besoin de l'autre et en même temps de peur de l'avenir. De mauvais choix et de pertes.
Isabelle, l'après midi est à mes yeux LE roman de l'auteur. Celui qu'il ne faut pas rater.

Tahukah kamu kalau CK Woo sudah memiliki impian besar di usia 14 tahun?⁠
===⁠
Flashback⁠
CK Woo sudah menekuni bidang jam tangan sejak usia muda. Pada tahun 1959 seorang datang ingin melakukan grafir pada jam tangan yang dipakainya sehari-hari. Orang itu ingin menggrafir tulisan "Martha1959" yang merupakan nama istrinya dan tahun meninggalnya.⁠
Orang tersebut ingin menggrafirnya karena agar bisa terus mengenang istrinya, dan selalu merasa istrinya bersamanya.⁠
Itulah merupakan tulisan grafir pertama dari CK Woo, dan merupakan latar belakangnya dalam membuat jam tangan berkualitas yang memberikan makna bagi setiap pemiliknya.⁠
===⁠

Ten Years After are a British hard rock blues band, most popular in the late 1960s and early 1970s. Between 1968 and 1973, Ten Years After scored eight Top 40 albums on the UK Albums Chart. In addition, they had twelve albums enter the US Billboard 200. 
Seen here is a minty 1969 UK press of ‘Ssssh.’, the bands third studio album. The same month of ‘Ssssh’s’ release found Ten Years After performing a career-making set at the historic @woodstock Festival, and the resulting publicity and acclaim put them on the map, boosting the new album all the way to No. 20 on the Billboard 200 and No. 4 back home in the U.K.
Although a short album, it is heavily laden with 60’s blues rock energy. If you get a chance, help yourself and listen to this era defining band. 🤘🏼🤫🤫🤫🎶🎶🎶🎶🔥

🇻🇪Buenas! Esta es la Jerrari #Wagoneer de #1970, una #loca idea de un magnate llamado William F Harrah, que quería ir a su finca cerca del Lago Tahoe con estilo y performance pero en un todoterreno. Harrah pidió a Enzo Ferrari que hiciera una versión One Of de un #Ferrari sobre una Wagoneer. Ferrari se negó y Harrah, siendo ingeniero mecánico, hizo su proyecto por su cuenta, toma una Jeep Wagoneer de 1970, una SUV lujosa para aquel momento, mantiene carrocería, chassis, suspensión y #4x4 y le monta la trompa de un Ferrari 365 GT de 1969, también toma del Ferrari el motor #V12 de 4.4 lts. Además un joyero de la ciudad de Las Vegas le hizo en metal Pulido la letra J para reemplazar la Ferrari y así paso a llamarse Jerrari. Además reemplazo el Cavalino de Ferrari por la caricatura de "Eugene the Jeep", a la cual muchos atribuyen el nombre "Jeep" del vehículo militar de Willys. Luego de años de desaparecida, fue comprada en 2008 por un coleccionista privado por $20300. Excelente día!
__________________________________________________________________________
🇬🇧Hello! This is the 1970 Jerrari Wagoneer, a #crazy idea of a millionaire call William f Harrah, who wanted to go to his estate near lake Tahoe with style, performance and all in a 4x4. Harrah asked Enzo Ferrari to make a One-off of a Ferrari mounted on a Jeep Wagoneer, Ferrari said no and Harrah, being a mechanical engineer built the #vehicle by his own. He took a 1970 Jeep Wagoneer, a luxurious #SUV by that time, kept the body, chassis, suspension and 4x4 and then replaced the front end with a front end of a 1969 Ferrari 365 GT, from which he also took the full point for V12 engine. Also a jeweler from Las Vegas made a polished metal letter J to replace the F in the name Ferrari, thus the name became Jerrari, he also replaced the Ferrari logo with an image of "Eugene the Jeep", who according to many, is the origin show the name Jeep of the Willys military vehicle. After years lost, it reappeared in 2008 when a private collector bought it for $20,300. Have a wonderful day!

03-06-1977 Nasce Checco Zalone.
Luca Pasquale Medici è un comico, cabarettista, attore, imitatore, cantautore, musicista, sceneggiatore e regista italiano. Nacque nella periferia Bari, e proprio dal dialetto barese deriva il suo nome d’arte: Checco Zalone infatti ricorda l'espressione "che cozzalone!", il cui equivalente e ben più noto significato, tratto dall’espressione barese significherebbe: "che tamarro!". Laureato in giurisprudenza, partecipa ai concorsi da vice ispettore di Polizia e all'Inail a Rimini, ma viene bocciato. Nel 2005 viene lanciato da Zelig e l’anno successivo riscuote un successo inaspettato con la canzone “Siamo una squadra fortissimi”. 03-06-1998 Manifestazioni piazza Tien An Men.
Il governo cinese soffoca la protesta degli studenti in piazza Tien An Men a Pechino contrapponendo i carri armati alla richiesta di riforme democratiche. L'intervento armato causerà la morte di un numero imprecisato di persone (tra 80 e 200) e circa settemila feriti.

03-06-1924 Muore Franz Kafka.
Franz Kafka è stato uno scrittore e filosofo boemo di lingua tedesca. è ritenuto una delle maggiori figure della letteratura del XX secolo e importante esponente del modernismo e del realismo magico. Il suo più celebre personaggio allegorico è lo scarafaggio umanoide Gregor Samsa, descritto ne La Metamorfosi.

Il 03 Giugno è la Giornata Mondiale della Bicicletta. Istituita nel 2018, come giornata ufficiale delle Nazioni Unite per la consapevolezza dei benefici sociali derivanti dall'uso della bicicletta come mezzo di trasporto e per il tempo libero.

「 SLOWHAND 35th Anniversary Deluxe Edition  Eric Clapton 」2012年12月19日発売 ( オリジナル 1977年11月 ) 。最新リマスター、DISC 2 ライヴ・アット・ハマースミス・オデオン 1977年4月27日 ダイジェスト全9曲収録 。

今まで、この作品をレコード、CD、紙ジャケット、SHM-CD と聴いてきたのだが、音が悪かった ( あくまで主観 ) 。

そこで、最新リマスターと見て ( もう最後 ) という覚悟の上で購入、聴いてみたのだが、おっとリマスター効果ありと嬉しくなった。以前は、平べったいサウンドにどうにかならんもんかと思っていたところにやっとだ。

しかも、クラプトンのサウンドをいじりすぎず丁度いい感じに音圧、音量も上がっている。そして DISC 2 は、LIVE音源まで収録されていて価格も2枚組にしては安い。スローハンドは、彼の代表作であり通称ブラッキー ( Fender Stratcaster Black Color ) が、またカッコいいのだ。

Day 1

When I was 13 I found a $100 bill on the sidewalk. I used it to buy my first Album with my own money (or whoever’s money it was I found) - an Electric Light Orchestra Out of the Blue double vinyl LP. I put the rest rest of the money in the bank. Spent it on my wedding years later (see yesterday’s posts). This is perfection - it’s probably my all-around, most played album ever. So memorable: the harmony, the hooks, the strings, the synthesizers, and  lyrics about love, loss, the big city, rain, and jungle animals singing and dancing in a dream(!). Jeff Lynne is a global treasure - he wrote & produced this album - and his voice and stellar guitar work is magic. There’s a reason John Lennon said he loved ELO. This album proves why. 
Jennifer Savinski Hatfield challenged me to post 10 albums that have influenced my musical taste - one record a day for 10 days with no explanation. I’ve always wanted to do this but was never nominated until now. YES! I can’t just do 10 though, I’m going to steal my buddy Fenner Castner’s idea and post as many as I can think of. Stay tuned, many great LPs coming! 💡

Another musician making his debut in ’73 was a singer called Tom Waits. Waits’ now classic album ‘Closing Time’ introduced the world to the trademark whiskey soaked croon of this Californian troubadour. Though initially performing poorly in a commercial sense, the album would go on to establish Waits as a significant new talent on the early 70’s singer-songwriter scene. ‘Ol’ 55’ would be covered a year later by The Eagles on their ‘On The Border’ album, and Tim Buckley would cover ‘Martha’ on his album ‘Sinfonia’. Songs such as ‘Virginia Avenue’, ‘Ice Cream Man’ and ‘Grapefruit Moon’ hint at the Beat Generation influence that would come to colour Waits’ most distinguished work. While Tom Waits is now perhaps best known for the experimentalist leanings of his later work, his debut ‘Closing Time’ remains a particularly endearing and memorable record.

🍍 Australia’s first fifty dollar note (aka “pineapple”) features the smiling face of pathologist Howard Walter Florey, instrumental in the advance of antibiotics. The fifty dollar note is the only place you will ever see anyone smile on an #aussie banknote. Next to Florey is a montage of imagery of his life - most of which are actually in England. The window, statue, college name, test tubes, etc are all taken from Oxford. The window and statue are from the library at Queen’s College there. So, along with the smiling, the fifty is also the only place you’ll see a foreign country in an Australian banknote. The theme of this note, released in 1973, is definitely “science”. The note was designed by Gordon Andrews, his last, and released later than the others in response to inflation. The flip side features Sir Ian Clunies Ross, father of Australia’s scientific boom and CSIRO - the organization who later pioneered polymer banknotes. Next to Clunies Ross is the Parkes Radio Telescope. Which is in NSW, rather than England. Whew. #australia #intaglio #banknotes #money #science #art #1970s #design #pineapple

Bewitched episode 'Sisters at Heart' was praised because of it’s anti-racism intention.‬ ‪The story was written by 22 African-American students from a tenth grade English class at Jefferson High School.

Elizabeth Montgomery and husband William Asher, the director of the episode, had the students visit the set.‬ Most students at the school were unable to read, write, or comprehend at a high school level, with 44% reading at a third grade level.

Sargent said that the students, "who might have been stuck in the ghetto for the rest of their lives, loved Bewitched, and with just a little approval and motivation, came alive on the set.

Montgomery considered "Sisters at Heart" her favorite episode of the series, and said that it "was created in the true spirit of Christmas ... conceived in the image of innocence and filled with truth." The episode received the Governors Award at the 23rd Primetime Emmy Awards ceremony in 1971.

was released carded as part of the seventh series (1988). He was also sold in 1989 and discontinued domestically in 1990.

File Name: Natale, Gregory M.

Birthplace: Wolfboro, New Hampshire
Primary Specialty: Arctic Warfare Training Instructor
Secondary Specialty: Infantry

Blizzard led an experimental security team based at Thule, Greenland for an entire winter. Their objective was to determine what kind of training and conditioning worked best to prepare men for combat in Arctic conditions. They found that training and conditioning had little effect. Only the hardest and meanest men made it through the course, and Blizzard was the hardest and meanest of the bunch. "The Arctic is totally unforgiving, You make one little mistake, you've had it. The cold makes you tired, and being tired makes you careless, and being careless makes you a statistic. #SteveMcQueen's five films of “#SmallAxe” tell “personal stories about #London’s #WestIndian community from the late-#1960s to mid-#1980s. The two entries selected for #CannesFilmFestival are “#LoversRock”- a fictional story of young #love and #music at a #blues party in the early 1980s,  and “#Mangrove" - the #truestory of the #Mangrove9 and the trial that took place at the Old Bailey in 1970. #throwbackthursday I’ve not really slept, my head hits the pillow and all the ill’s of the world swirl around constantly in my brain, I write and rewrite, I try to formulate, I try to understand, I seek answers, I pose questions, I feel pain. Because injustice is pain, hatred is pain. This beautiful photo taken by @alicehobbsbailey Saturday lunchtime in Leeds, people would hangout at Farmhouse kitchen, me and the girls here , were 15, the guys our pals from going out to Funk and Soul days and nights, places like Tiffany’s, Central Park etc. When Alice shared this last year it was a joy to see. Bottom right is Marta, she joined our high school and we bonded as I’d heard of Sierra Leone, mainly as my parents had worked with someone from there in the early 1970s. She was adopted. That day she’d called for me and we’d walked into town, met everyone at FHC hung out and then we’d gone off for a mooch around the shops. In those days the National Front, gathered near W.H.Smiths selling their hate mag and being *nts , there was a line in town, unmarked, but dangerous territory if you weren’t white. We were near it, suddenly a mob in the distance started running our way, we looked at each other, not properly comprehending it was us they were after. Penny drops and we are running for our lives. Leeds is known for it’s beautiful Victorian arcades , we shot down one, the noise of the attack men behind us, to our horror, there are more coming up the arcade, hate carved into each face, writing this I see and feel it with movie clarity. Fuck, we’re fucked, literally swallowing your heart, sick with fear. A door opens, a shopkeeper pulls us in and bolts the door.  Male I think, how did they know? Whoever they were, they saved us, we were lucky. My mind is blank after that. Two teenage girls escaping men who were driven by hatred because one of the girls was black.  I have a lot of stories as do my friends.  #blacklivesmatter #humanity #equality #injustice #blackhistory #antiracist #citystories #blackandwhiteunite #1980s

Cool Prototype C-3PO!
Waaaaait a minute... This is what happens when you leave a regular production C-3PO in some brake fluid for a day or two. That solution peels the vacuum formed gold paint right off to expose what was used underneath. Some figures have cool multicolour plastics and some... like this one, have rather drab colours that are neat but not super exciting. It’s a fun thing to try if you have some beater C-3PO’s (DON’T ruin a good figure!!).

80 paintings 122 x 122 cm.
125 paintings 61 x 52 cm.
Alkyd, alkyd enamel, pigment on hardboard.
All produced in 1988.

#floradanica #stigbrøgger #stigbroegger #artist #art #artwork #painting #contemporaryart #artoftheday #museum #1990 @smkmuseum #smkmuseum ⁠
------------⁠
Jean François Lyotard on Flora Danica: ⁠
"I see a tension in the co-existence of heterogeneous gestures, two in the simplest case but possibly more. They can be at work in the same piece, but can also work across different pieces of the whole series [...] On the one hand you have the rule of geometry, on the other a thrust of colour with no obvious rules [...] That then could be the essence of flora. It subjects plants born of the wild womb of the earth to systematic description and taxonomy [...] Flora is the result of two silences, the grace of nature and the violence of law, which it does not resolve" (Lyotard’s text reprinted in Stig Brøgger. Now Here. Strandberg Publishing, 2019) @strandbergpublishing

Today In 1996, Metallica Released Their 6th Album "Load" Through Elektra Records & Vertigo Records.

The Album, Released Approximately 5 Years After The Commercially Successful Album "Metallica" (1991), Saw The Band Shifting Toward Hard Rock & Away From Their Thrash Metal Roots. As On Previous Releases, The Album's 14 Songs Began As Rough Demos Created By Principal Songwriters, Frontman/Rhythm Guitarist James Hetfield & Drummer Lars Ulrich, In Ulrich's Basement Recording Studio, "The Dungeon". In Early 1995, The Band Took Over 30 Demos Into The Plant Studios In Sausalito, California, Where They Would Work For Approximately 1 Year.

Metallica Worked With Producer Bob Rock, Who Had Been At The Helm During The Recording Process For "Metallica". The Songwriting Dispenses Almost Entirely With The Thrash Metal Style That Characterized The Band's Sound In The 1980s. In Place Of Staccato Riffs, Hetfield & Lead Guitarist Kirk Hammett Experimented awith Blues Rock-Based Tones & Styles. Additionally, Lars Ulrich Adopted A Minimalist Approach To His Drum Recording, Abandoning The Speed & Complex Double Bass Drumming Patterns Of Previous Albums, & Using Simpler Techniques & Playing Styles. 
James Hetfield Displayed A Lyrical Evolution, Writing What Many Said Were His Most Personal & Introspective Lyrics. Kirk Hammett, Encouraged By Producer Bob Rock, Also Played Rhythm Guitar On A Metallica Album For The 1st Time, Having Previously Only Played Lead Parts With Hetfield Playing All The Rhythm Parts To Achieve A Tighter Feel, In Contrast To The Looser Feel They Were Looking For Here. At 79 Minutes, "Load" Is Metallica's Longest Studio Album. "Load" Peaked @ Number 1 On The Billboard 200 Chart In 1996, Becoming Certified 5x Platinum By The RIAA In The US For Selling 5,000,000^ Copies. The Album Received Positive To Mixed Reviews From Critics.

глава 7

А—Можешь ответить мне на один вопрос?

М—Валяй—Продолжая следить за дорогой.

А—Нахуя я тебе нужна? 
Он промолчал, тем самым не ответил на мой вопрос. Всю оставшуюся дорогу мы ехали в тишине. Чтобы не так скучно было, я включила музыку.

Доехали быстро, пробок не было. Выйдя из машины, зашли в лифт, поднялись на наш этаж. И как только мы зашли, он быстро закрыл дверь и прижал меня к стене.

М—Я же говорил, что вечером продолжим—Шепча на ухо и обжигая мою кожу горячим дыханием.

После страстно целовал мои губы и иногда переходил на шею, улыбнувшись сквозь поцелуй, Марк подхватил меня за бедра и понёс в спальню. Он лихорадочно покрывал мою шею поцелуями, в некоторых местах покусывая и посасывая, тем самым оставляя там большие метки. Мне было максимально неприятно, поэтому я не могла поддержать его действия, но после нескольких пощёчин мне всё-таки пришлось это сделать. Вот с моих губ слетает первый стон. Сразу же чувствую его улыбку. Руки блуждали по моему телу... Забравшись руками под толстовку он начал гладить мою спину. Сняв эту самую толстовку, которая явно ему мешала, Марк кинул меня на кровать. Стянув с меня футболку брюнет дошёл до кружевного лифчика, завел руки за спину и расстегнул его. Спустив шлейки он выкинул ненужный атрибут одежды на пол. Снова страстно целует, врываясь своим языком в мой рот, поглаживая нёбо и вырисовывая всевозможные узоры во рту. Сняв с себя ненужную одежду, продолжил свои действия... Своими поцелуями он спускался всё ниже и ниже... Дойдя до ямочки пупка, обвел ее языком... Проложив дорожку поцелуев до края джинс, он провел рукой по внутренней стороне бедра и быстро снял штаны и кружевные трусики. Избавившись от своих боксеров он снова поцеловал меня. Удобно пристроившись между ног, он погладил меня по лобку и резко вошел. Из-за этого с горла вырвался крик, а с глаз покатились слёзы... Через считаные минуты вместо боли приходит наслаждение и из моей грудной клетки вырывается тихий стон наслаждения... Вцепившись в спину парня, оставляю на ней красные полосы... Еще несколько толчков и он достигает пика, замер, и с рычанием излился на простынь кровати.

LA RIPRESA

Approfittando della riapertura tra regioni e la non ripresa del lavoro, insieme a mia moglie siamo scesi in Abruzzo per rivedere i miei genitori. Oggi, mentre ero a Lanciano a fare delle commissioni, sono rientrato dopo vent'anni in un negozio di musica che frequentavo sporadicamente quando ero ragazzino. 
Così, dando un'occhiata qua e là, ho (ri)trovato queste due perle della musica italiana degli anni '90: Linea Gotica dei CSI del 1996, che non ha bisogno di presentazioni e Gommalacca di Franco Battiato del 1998. Questo è uno degli album più sperimentali dell'artista catanese, infatti il sound spazia da un rock alternativo alla musica elettronica, passando per sfumature reggae. In questo disco Battiato si è avvalso della collaborazione di Morgan, Ginevra di Marco, Madaski e Ru Catania degli Africa Unite.
